INSERT INTO "picture" VALUES (111, 20201129, 202011291600, 20201130, 'https://cn.bing.com', '/th?id=OHR.EDCScotland_ZH-CN2038527689_1920x1080.jpg&rf=LaDigue_1920x1080.jpg&pid=hp', '/th?id=OHR.EDCScotland_ZH-CN2038527689_UHD.jpg&rf=LaDigue_UHD.jpg&pid=hp', '/th?id=OHR.EDCScotland_ZH-CN2038527689', 'OHR.EDCScotland_ZH-CN2038527689_1920x1080.jpg', 'OHR.EDCScotland_ZH-CN2038527689_UHD.jpg', '艾琳多南堡，苏格兰 (© CBW/Alamy)', NULL, 'https://www.bing.com/search?q=%E8%89%BE%E7%90%B3%E5%A4%9A%E5%8D%97%E5%A0%A1&form=hpcapt&mkt=zh-cn', '', '/search?q=Bing+homepage+quiz&filters=WQOskey:%22HPQuiz_20201129_EDCScotland%22&FORM=HPQUIZ', 'true', '5722b022474c0954867b52951affaa9e', 1, 1, 1, '[]', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL);
INSERT INTO "picture" VALUES (144, 20201215, 202012151600, 20201216, 'https://cn.bing.com', '/th?id=OHR.MunnarMist_ZH-CN8816703625_1920x1080.jpg&rf=LaDigue_1920x1080.jpg&pid=hp', '/th?id=OHR.MunnarMist_ZH-CN8816703625_UHD.jpg&rf=LaDigue_UHD.jpg&pid=hp', '/th?id=OHR.MunnarMist_ZH-CN8816703625', 'OHR.MunnarMist_ZH-CN8816703625_1920x1080.jpg', 'OHR.MunnarMist_ZH-CN8816703625_UHD.jpg', '雾气环绕的森林，喀拉拉邦慕那尔市，印度 (© Ahammed Riswan/EyeEm/Getty Images)', 'Ludwig van Beethoven sculptures and monument at the Münsterplatz, Bonn, Germany (© dpa/Alamy Live News)', 'https://www.bing.com/search?q=ludwig+van+beethoven&form=hpcapt&filters=HpDate%3a%2220201216_0800%22', '', '/search?q=Bing+homepage+quiz&filters=WQOskey:%22HPQuiz_20201216_Beethoven250%22&FORM=HPQUIZ', 'true', '3665f65cc49fed4e82f04091f2734f8a', 1, 1, 1, '[]', 'Beethoven''s 250th', 'German composer Ludwig van Beethoven created melodies and harmonies we instantly recognize, even in this entertainment-saturated 21st century. Overcoming childhood abuse, hearing loss, romantic rejection, and bouts of depression and alcoholism, Beethoven channeled his stormy emotions into music that compelled audiences to viscerally feel what he felt. In the process, he helped end the regimented Classical era and usher in the Romantic period, where even the most flawed artists were sovereign. This scene at Bonn''s Münsterplatz features the city''s enduring Beethoven Monument (at rear), seemingly swarmed by an additional 700 green- and gold-colored Beethoven statues. Created by German conceptual artist Ottmar Hörl, the colorful statues were placed in the square last year in the run-up to the composer''s birthday. Beethoven concerts and celebrations had been planned in Germany and around the world throughout 2020 in honor of this milestone anniversary. Most have been pushed to next year due to the coronavirus pandemic, but with a quick Bing video search for your favorite symphony or sonata, you can join the world in appreciating Beethoven''s radical creativity.', '贝多芬的第250次', '德国作曲家路德维希·范·贝多芬创作了旋律和和声，我们立刻认出来，即使在这个娱乐饱和的21世纪。贝多芬克服了童年的虐待、听力损失、浪漫的排斥以及抑郁和酗酒的一轮，将他的暴风不由多的情绪引导到音乐中，迫使观众内心感受到他的感受。在这个过程中，他帮助结束了古典时代，迎来了浪漫主义时期，即使是最有缺陷的艺术家也是主权的。波恩的明斯特广场的这一幕以这座城市持久的贝多芬纪念碑（后方）为特征，似乎还有700尊绿色和金色的贝多芬雕像。这些五颜六色的雕像由德国概念艺术家Ottmar Hürl创作，去年在作曲家生日前被放置在广场上。贝多芬音乐会和庆祝活动已计划在德国和世界各地在整个2020年，以纪念这一里程碑式周年纪念日。由于冠状病毒大流行，大多数被推到明年，但通过快速的必应视频搜索你最喜欢的交响乐或奏鸣曲，你可以与全世界一起欣赏贝多芬的激进创造力。');
INSERT INTO "picture" VALUES (145, 20201214, 202012141600, 20201215, 'https://cn.bing.com', '/th?id=OHR.ElbeBastei_ZH-CN9708654240_1920x1080.jpg&rf=LaDigue_1920x1080.jpg&pid=hp', '/th?id=OHR.ElbeBastei_ZH-CN9708654240_UHD.jpg&rf=LaDigue_UHD.jpg&pid=hp', '/th?id=OHR.ElbeBastei_ZH-CN9708654240', 'OHR.ElbeBastei_ZH-CN9708654240_1920x1080.jpg', 'OHR.ElbeBastei_ZH-CN9708654240_UHD.jpg', '易北河上的巴斯泰桥，德国撒克逊瑞士国家公园 (© Reinhard Schmid/eStock Photo)', 'Bastei Bridge above the Elbe river in Saxon Switzerland National Park, Germany (© Reinhard Schmid/eStock Photo)', 'https://www.bing.com/search?q=bastei+bridge&FORM=hpcapt&filters=HpDate%3a%2220201215_0800%22', '', '/search?q=Bing+homepage+quiz&filters=WQOskey:%22HPQuiz_20201215_ElbeBastei%22&FORM=HPQUIZ', 'true', '38a3f7597635416b65b0da33ad5670d6', 1, 1, 1, '[]', 'A bridge that rocks', 'Sandwiched between soaring pinnacles of sandstone, Bastei Bridge is a highlight of Saxon Switzerland National Park. But don''t be fooled by the park''s name because we''re not in Switzerland; we''re hundreds of miles away in eastern Germany, close to the border of the Czech Republic. The name comes from two Swiss artists who visited the area in the second half of the 18th century and felt the picturesque upland scenery was reminiscent of their homeland. The park boasts untamed forests and spectacular rock formations, including the Bastei in our photo. The rock pillars here were formed by water erosion over a million years ago and tower 636 feet above the Elbe, one of the major rivers in Central Europe. If you''re not afraid of heights, you can walk the bridge that has connected these jagged rocks for almost 200 years. Originally made of wood but rebuilt with stone in 1851 to accommodate the increasing tourist traffic, Bastei Bridge offers stunning panoramic views of the river and surrounding Elbe Sandstone Mountains. It also leads to the remains of an ancient castle that once stood here and is now an open-air museum.', '岩石桥', '巴斯特大桥夹在高耸的砂岩顶点之间，是撒克逊瑞士国家公园的亮点。但不要被公园的名字愚弄，因为我们不在瑞士;我们在德国东部几百英里外，靠近捷克共和国的边界。这个名字来自两位瑞士艺术家，他们在18世纪下半叶参观了该地区，觉得风景如画的高地景色让人想起他们的祖国。公园拥有未驯服的森林和壮观的岩层，包括我们照片中的巴斯蒂。这里的岩石柱是由一百多万年前的水蚀形成的，在中欧主要河流之一的伊贝河上高636英尺高。如果你不怕高度，你可以走桥，连接这些锯齿状的岩石近200年。Bastei桥最初由木材制成，但在1851年用石头重建，以适应不断增长的旅游交通，提供河流和周围的埃尔贝砂岩山脉的迷人全景。它也导致一个古老的城堡的遗迹，曾经站在这里，现在是一个露天博物馆。');
INSERT INTO "picture" VALUES (146, 20201213, 202012131600, 20201214, 'https://cn.bing.com', '/th?id=OHR.PineGrosbeak_ZH-CN9629000282_1920x1080.jpg&rf=LaDigue_1920x1080.jpg&pid=hp', '/th?id=OHR.PineGrosbeak_ZH-CN9629000282_UHD.jpg&rf=LaDigue_UHD.jpg&pid=hp', '/th?id=OHR.PineGrosbeak_ZH-CN9629000282', 'OHR.PineGrosbeak_ZH-CN9629000282_1920x1080.jpg', 'OHR.PineGrosbeak_ZH-CN9629000282_UHD.jpg', '松雀 (© Peter Lilja/Getty Images)', 'Pine grosbeak (© Peter Lilja/Getty Images)', 'https://www.bing.com/search?q=pine+grosbeak&form=hpcapt&filters=HpDate%3a%2220201214_0800%22', '', '/search?q=Bing+homepage+quiz&filters=WQOskey:%22HPQuiz_20201214_PineGrosbeak%22&FORM=HPQUIZ', 'true', '5fffc8375e1ca3eb1352a02db3abe65a', 1, 1, 1, '[]', 'I see one!', 'Today''s the first day of the 120th annual Christmas Bird Count, said to be the largest and longest-running citizen science project in the world. For the next 23 days, through January 5, thousands of volunteers around the US, Canada, Latin America, the Caribbean, and Pacific Islands will join members of the Audubon Society for this important endeavor in the study and protection of birds. Together, they''ll scour the woods, fields, and lakes of their respective regions (or just watch their bird feeders), to take a census of the individual birds and species they find. Bird watchers in Western Canada, Alaska, and the Northwest United States will undoubtably find a few pine grosbeaks like the one featured in our image today. The largest member of the true finch family, it makes its nest in the northern boreal forests and feeds on berries and fruits. You might identify it from its short musical warble. While the pine grosbeak mostly stays in the northern latitudes, it''s an irruptive species, meaning it migrates some winters farther south to find food. It''s quite tame and unafraid of people, so it can be easy to overlook because it''ll often sit still as a bird watcher walks by. If you''re contributing to this year''s Christmas Bird Count—and even if you''re not—keep an eye out for this beauty.', '我看到一个！', '今天是第120届圣诞鸟计数的第一天，据说是世界上最大和持续时间最长的公民科学项目。在未来23天，到1月5日，来自美国、加拿大、拉丁美洲、加勒比和太平洋群岛的数千名志愿者将加入奥杜邦协会的成员，为鸟类的研究和保护这一重要努力。它们一起搜索各自地区的树林、田野和湖泊（或只是观察他们的鸟类喂食者），以普查他们找到的鸟类和物种。加拿大西部、阿拉斯加州和美国西北部的观鸟者将毫无疑问地发现一些松树，就像今天我们形象中所示。作为真正的雀家族的最大成员，它在北方的北方森林筑巢，以浆果和水果为食。你可以从它短暂的音乐扭曲中辨认出它。松树大部分停留在北纬，它是一种易怒的物种，这意味着它迁徙一些冬天更远的南方寻找食物。它相当驯服，不怕人，所以很容易被忽视，因为它经常会坐着不动，作为一个观鸟者走过。如果你正在为今年的圣诞鸟计数做贡献——即使你没有——请留意这个美。');
INSERT INTO "picture" VALUES (147, 20201212, 202012121600, 20201213, 'https://cn.bing.com', '/th?id=OHR.PolarExpress_ZH-CN9522496479_1920x1080.jpg&rf=LaDigue_1920x1080.jpg&pid=hp', '/th?id=OHR.PolarExpress_ZH-CN9522496479_UHD.jpg&rf=LaDigue_UHD.jpg&pid=hp', '/th?id=OHR.PolarExpress_ZH-CN9522496479', 'OHR.PolarExpress_ZH-CN9522496479_1920x1080.jpg', 'OHR.PolarExpress_ZH-CN9522496479_UHD.jpg', '戈尔内格拉特火车站和马特洪峰，瑞士采尔马特 (© coolbiere photograph/Getty Images)', 'Gornergrat railway station and the Matterhorn in Zermatt, Switzerland (© coolbiere photograph/Getty Images)', 'https://www.bing.com/search?q=gornergrat+train+station&form=hpcapt&filters=HpDate%3a%2220201213_0800%22', '', '/search?q=Bing+homepage+quiz&filters=WQOskey:%22HPQuiz_20201213_PolarExpress%22&FORM=HPQUIZ', 'true', '2f595ee4c5b6caf662f6697850e29e24', 1, 1, 1, '[]', 'The view will stop you in your tracks', 'When it comes to beautiful winter scenery, Switzerland is hard to beat. We''re looking at the Gornergrat railway with the peak of the Matterhorn in the background. One of the last great peaks of the Alps to be climbed by humans, the Matterhorn was finally summited in 1865, capping off the decade or so that''s been called the ''golden age of alpinism.'' The iconic peak is a daunting pyramid of stone and ice, towering just inside Switzerland''s border with Italy. The train goes from the village center in Zermatt (at an altitude of 5,200 feet) to Gornergrat (over 10,000 feet) in 33 minutes, offering incredible views along the way. The train debuted in 1898 as the world''s first fully electric cog railway, connecting three existing hotels. The new attraction helped to make Zermatt a popular tourist destination, and by the time the railway began winter operations in 1928, this corner of the high Alps had become a glamorous year-round vacation hotspot.', '视图将阻止您跟踪', '说到美丽的冬季风景，瑞士是很难击败的。我们正在看戈纳格拉特铁路与马特霍恩的高峰的背景。作为阿尔卑斯山最后一座由人类攀登的高峰之一，马特霍恩终于在1865年登顶，结束了被称为"阿尔卑斯山黄金时代"的十年左右。标志性的山峰是一座令人生畏的石头和冰金字塔，高耸在瑞士与意大利的边界内。火车从采尔马特的村中心（海拔 5，200 英尺）到戈尔纳格拉特（超过 10，000 英尺），在 33 分钟内，沿途提供令人难以置信的景色。这列火车于1898年首开，是世界上第一条全电动的铁路，连接着三家现有酒店。新的景点使采尔马特成为一个受欢迎的旅游目的地，当铁路在1928年开始冬季运营时，阿尔卑斯山的这个角落已成为迷人的全年度假热点。');
INSERT INTO "picture" VALUES (148, 20201211, 202012111600, 20201212, 'https://cn.bing.com', '/th?id=OHR.BractCloseup_ZH-CN9096611979_1920x1080.jpg&rf=LaDigue_1920x1080.jpg&pid=hp', '/th?id=OHR.BractCloseup_ZH-CN9096611979_UHD.jpg&rf=LaDigue_UHD.jpg&pid=hp', '/th?id=OHR.BractCloseup_ZH-CN9096611979', 'OHR.BractCloseup_ZH-CN9096611979_1920x1080.jpg', 'OHR.BractCloseup_ZH-CN9096611979_UHD.jpg', '一品红叶子特写 (© Charles Floyd/Alamy)', 'Poinsettia leaf close-up (© Charles Floyd/Alamy)', 'https://www.bing.com/search?q=Poinsettia&form=hpcapt&filters=HpDate%3a%2220201212_0800%22', '', '/search?q=Bing+homepage+quiz&filters=WQOskey:%22HPQuiz_20201212_BractCloseup%22&FORM=HPQUIZ', 'true', 'da9e9a1fb03068b94ffeb874fe334fee', 1, 1, 1, '[]', 'What are we looking at?', 'On National Poinsettia Day we''re taking an up-close look at a poinsettia leaf. Although many people assume the red, white, pink, purple, or marbled colors are flowers, they''re actually bracts, a type of leaf that aids in reproduction, usually by turning color as the plant develops true flowers. On the poinsettia, the bracts, surrounding small yellow clustered buds called cyathia, flag down pollinators just as flower petals do. And while we''re talking poinsettias, let''s dispel a dark myth about this cheerful holiday plant: They are not fatally toxic to children and pets. Way back in 1971, an Ohio State study determined that a 50-pound child would have to eat about 500 leaves to see any ill effects. Those ill effects? Let''s just say they''re of a gastrointestinal variety and leave it at that.', '我们在看什么？', '在国宾塞蒂亚日，我们将近距离地看一下一片庞塞蒂娅的叶子。虽然许多人认为红色、白色、粉红色、紫色或大理石色是花，但它们实际上是一种有助于繁殖的叶子，通常通过植物开发真花时变色。在花瓣上，胸围，周围的小黄色簇芽称为环花，降旗授粉者就像花瓣一样。当我们谈论庞塞蒂亚斯时，让我们揭开关于这种欢快的节日植物的黑暗神话：它们对孩子和宠物没有致命的毒性。早在1971年，俄亥俄州的一项研究就确定，一个50磅重的孩子必须吃大约500片叶子才能看到任何不良后果。那些不良后果？让我们说， 他们是一个胃肠道品种， 并留在那。');
INSERT INTO "picture" VALUES (149, 20201210, 202012101600, 20201211, 'https://cn.bing.com', '/th?id=OHR.QueenoftheAndes_ZH-CN9019108680_1920x1080.jpg&rf=LaDigue_1920x1080.jpg&pid=hp', '/th?id=OHR.QueenoftheAndes_ZH-CN9019108680_UHD.jpg&rf=LaDigue_UHD.jpg&pid=hp', '/th?id=OHR.QueenoftheAndes_ZH-CN9019108680', 'OHR.QueenoftheAndes_ZH-CN9019108680_1920x1080.jpg', 'OHR.QueenoftheAndes_ZH-CN9019108680_UHD.jpg', '以布兰卡山脉为背景的安地斯皇后（莴氏普亚凤梨），秘鲁 (© Cyril Ruoso/Minden Pictures)', 'Queen of the Andes plants with the Cordillera Blanca massif in the background, Peru (© Cyril Ruoso/Minden Pictures)', 'https://www.bing.com/search?q=international+mountain+day+united+nations&form=hpcapt&filters=HpDate%3a%2220201211_0800%22', '', '/search?q=Bing+homepage+quiz&filters=WQOskey:%22HPQuiz_20201211_QueenoftheAndes%22&FORM=HPQUIZ', 'true', 'f82f1fb22056e750166a578712b6a804', 1, 1, 1, '[]', 'Mountains fit for a queen', 'Like sentinels standing guard, these towering stalks are flowers of the queen of the Andes, the world''s largest bromeliad—some specimens can grow up to 50 feet tall. This extraordinary plant has adapted to grow only in the adverse conditions found on the high slopes of the Bolivian and Peruvian Andes. To see several of them in bloom at once is truly special, for the queen of the Andes sends up her flowering stalk just once, after a century or so of painstaking growth. A single plant will bloom for about three months, producing anywhere from 8,000 to 20,000 flowers, then die. Because mountains present a variety of altitudes, exposures, and gradients, they host a broad spectrum of climatic zones and ecosystems. The plants in our image are thriving in Peru''s Cordillera Blanca (White Range), the highest and most glaciated tropical mountain range in the world. Several peaks in the Cordillera Blanca tower more than 20,000 feet in elevation, making it a world-class climbing destination. Each step up or down in altitude seems to introduce a new ecosystem, with plants and animals that have adapted to each differentiated zone. Protecting this biodiversity found on mountains is the theme for 2020''s International Mountain Day, held each year on December 11. The UN, which founded International Mountain Day, invites us to join the conversation about the importance of mountains. On social media, use the hashtag #MountainsMatter to share about the biodiversity in the mountains near you.', '山适合女王', '像哨兵站岗一样，这些高耸的茎是荷兰女王的花朵，而荷兰女王是世界上最大的溴化物——有些标本可以长到50英尺高。这种非凡的植物已经适应生长，只有在玻利维亚和秘鲁安第斯山脉的高坡的不利条件下生长。看到其中几个花一次是真正特殊的，因为安迪斯女王送她的开花茎只是一次，经过一个世纪左右的艰苦成长。一种植物将开花约三个月，产生8000至20，000朵花，然后死亡。由于山脉呈现各种海拔、暴露和梯度，因此它们拥有广泛的气候区和生态系统。我们形象中的植物在秘鲁的科迪莱拉布兰卡（白山脉）茁壮成长，这是世界上最高和最冰川化的热带山脉。科迪莱拉布兰卡塔的几座山峰海拔超过 20，000 英尺，因此成为世界级的登山目的地。海拔的每一步上升或下降似乎都引入了一个新的生态系统，植物和动物已经适应了每个分化区域。保护山上的生物多样性是每年12月11日举行的2020年国际山地日的主题。联合国创立了国际山区日，它邀请我们参加关于山区重要性的对话。在社交媒体上，使用标签#MountainsMatter分享您附近山区的生物多样性。');
INSERT INTO "picture" VALUES (150, 20201209, 202012091600, 20201210, 'https://cn.bing.com', '/th?id=OHR.SleepingArcticFox_ZH-CN8743925021_1920x1080.jpg&rf=LaDigue_1920x1080.jpg&pid=hp', '/th?id=OHR.SleepingArcticFox_ZH-CN8743925021_UHD.jpg&rf=LaDigue_UHD.jpg&pid=hp', '/th?id=OHR.SleepingArcticFox_ZH-CN8743925021', 'OHR.SleepingArcticFox_ZH-CN8743925021_1920x1080.jpg', 'OHR.SleepingArcticFox_ZH-CN8743925021_UHD.jpg', '正在睡觉的北极狐 (© Menno Schaefer/Getty Images)', 'Sleeping Arctic fox (© Menno Schaefer/Getty Images)', 'https://www.bing.com/search?q=arctic+fox&form=hpcapt&filters=HpDate%3a%2220201210_0800%22', '', '/search?q=Bing+homepage+quiz&filters=WQOskey:%22HPQuiz_20201210_SleepingArcticFox%22&FORM=HPQUIZ', 'true', 'bae56de46fb3b120731431699fc8a861', 1, 1, 1, '[]', 'What does the fox dream?', 'We''re sure you could just squeeze this snoozing Arctic fox like a stuffed animal, but we wouldn''t advise it. These cute little fuzzballs can be ferocious hunters. In fact, the Arctic fox is one of the most prolific predators on the tundra, preying on lemmings, voles, rabbits, birds (often with a side of eggs), and other small critters that cross their adorable path. But right now, our Arctic fox is happy to curl up with its tail and get some shuteye—by forming a ball with its body, the fox is exposing the least possible surface area to cold air, helping to conserve heat no matter how low the mercury dips.', '狐狸梦到什么了？', '我们确信你可以像填充动物一样挤压这只打盹的北极狐， 但我们不建议这样做。这些可爱的小模糊球可以是凶猛的猎人。事实上，北极狐是冻土带上最多产的食肉动物之一，捕食着莱明斯、狼、兔子、鸟类（通常有鸡蛋的一侧）和其他穿过它们可爱的小路的小动物。但是现在，我们的北极狐乐于用尾巴卷曲起来，然后闭眼——通过用身体形成一个球，狐狸将尽可能小的表面暴露在冷空气中，帮助保存热量，无论汞含量有多低。');
INSERT INTO "picture" VALUES (151, 20201208, 202012081600, 20201209, 'https://cn.bing.com', '/th?id=OHR.Kinkakuji_ZH-CN8643828412_1920x1080.jpg&rf=LaDigue_1920x1080.jpg&pid=hp', '/th?id=OHR.Kinkakuji_ZH-CN8643828412_UHD.jpg&rf=LaDigue_UHD.jpg&pid=hp', '/th?id=OHR.Kinkakuji_ZH-CN8643828412', 'OHR.Kinkakuji_ZH-CN8643828412_1920x1080.jpg', 'OHR.Kinkakuji_ZH-CN8643828412_UHD.jpg', '冬天的金阁寺，日本京都 (© yoko_ken_chan/Shutterstock)', 'Kinkakuji temple in winter, Kyoto, Japan (© yoko_ken_chan/Shutterstock)', 'https://www.bing.com/search?q=Kinkakuji+temple&form=hpcapt&filters=HpDate%3a%2220201209_0800%22', '', '/search?q=Bing+homepage+quiz&filters=WQOskey:%22HPQuiz_20201209_Kinkakuji%22&FORM=HPQUIZ', 'true', 'cff29e1f3a0ba226c0fec677ad1f1be6', 1, 1, 1, '[]', 'Stunning in winter', 'Kinkakuji, also known as the Golden Pavilion, is one of the most famous sights in Kyoto. The golden temple that is actually made of gold, has been a popular attraction for many. During the winter, the white color of the snow contrasts beautifully with the color of the temple creating a breathtaking sight.', '冬季令人惊叹的', '金库吉，也被称为金亭，是京都最著名的景点之一。黄金寺庙实际上是由黄金，一直是许多人的热门景点。在冬季，雪的白色与寺庙的颜色形成鲜明对比，营造出令人叹为观止的景象。');
INSERT INTO "picture" VALUES (152, 20201207, 202012071600, 20201208, 'https://cn.bing.com', '/th?id=OHR.RoccaCalascio_ZH-CN8546031521_1920x1080.jpg&rf=LaDigue_1920x1080.jpg&pid=hp', '/th?id=OHR.RoccaCalascio_ZH-CN8546031521_UHD.jpg&rf=LaDigue_UHD.jpg&pid=hp', '/th?id=OHR.RoccaCalascio_ZH-CN8546031521', 'OHR.RoccaCalascio_ZH-CN8546031521_1920x1080.jpg', 'OHR.RoccaCalascio_ZH-CN8546031521_UHD.jpg', '阿布鲁佐的Rocca Calascio，意大利 (© Francesco Russo/eStock Photo)', 'Rocca Calascio in Abruzzo, Italy (© Francesco Russo/eStock Photo)', 'https://www.bing.com/search?q=rocca+calascio+italy&form=hpcapt&filters=HpDate%3a%2220201208_0800%22', '', '/search?q=Bing+homepage+quiz&filters=WQOskey:%22HPQuiz_20201208_RoccaCalascio%22&FORM=HPQUIZ', 'true', '03981560ffe0d9b0028701e6771d543f', 1, 1, 1, '[]', 'A fortress in the sky', 'Beginning as a lone watchtower high in the Apennines in the 10th century, the fortress called Rocca Calascio gained more heft over the next few hundred years. A quartet of additional towers and heavy walls were gradually added around the first tower. These fortifications made clear that Rocco Calascio was ready for any military rivals who might scale the slopes from the valley below to attack this garrison. The fight never came. The ruins you see here are not battle scars but the result of a powerful earthquakes. By the early 1700s, Rocca Calascio was abandoned, but it can still claim the title of highest fortress in the Apennines—and some of the most spectacular views in all of Italy. In fact, filmmakers have chosen the site for several movies, including ''The Name of the Rose'' and ''Ladyhawke.''', '天空中的堡垒', '从10世纪亚平宁的一座孤金瞭望塔开始，这座名为罗卡·卡拉西奥的堡垒在接下来的几百年里变得更加高。在第一座塔楼周围逐渐增加了四分之一的塔楼和沉重的墙壁。这些防御工事表明，罗科·卡拉西奥已经为任何可能从下面的山谷上扩大斜坡攻击这个驻军的军事对手做好准备。战斗从未来过。你在这里看到的废墟不是战斗的伤疤，而是强烈地震的结果。到17世纪早期，罗卡卡拉西奥被遗弃，但它仍然可以声称在亚彭宁斯最高的堡垒的称号 - 和一些在意大利最壮观的景色。事实上，电影制作人已经为几部电影选择了该网站，包括《玫瑰的名字》和《夫人霍克》。');
INSERT INTO "picture" VALUES (153, 20201206, 202012061600, 20201207, 'https://cn.bing.com', '/th?id=OHR.VogelhaeuserD_ZH-CN8437589222_1920x1080.jpg&rf=LaDigue_1920x1080.jpg&pid=hp', '/th?id=OHR.VogelhaeuserD_ZH-CN8437589222_UHD.jpg&rf=LaDigue_UHD.jpg&pid=hp', '/th?id=OHR.VogelhaeuserD_ZH-CN8437589222', 'OHR.VogelhaeuserD_ZH-CN8437589222_1920x1080.jpg', 'OHR.VogelhaeuserD_ZH-CN8437589222_UHD.jpg', '挂在树上的小鸟舍 (© Westend61/Getty Images)', 'Birdhouses hanging in a tree (© Westend61/Getty Images)', 'https://www.bing.com/search?q=bird+feeder&form=hpcapt&filters=HpDate%3a%2220201207_0800%22', '', '/search?q=Bing+homepage+quiz&filters=WQOskey:%22HPQuiz_20201207_VogelhaeuserD%22&FORM=HPQUIZ', 'true', 'fc0c496984483e1f1af8f6dbe90e737f', 1, 1, 1, '[]', 'Ready to feed', 'Feeding wild birds throughout winter (and especially around Christmas) has long been a tradition around much of Scandinavia. While the primary aim is to ensure the feathered friends have enough food to survive the long winter months, the creation of birdhouses serve another purpose as well - granting their creators a closer look at their many visitors. And as you can see from today’s image, when building a bird feeder the only limit is your imagination. The owner of this collection of feeders, for example, obviously expects heavy air traffic in the coming weeks. One can only hope that the birds won’t find it a difficult to choose which spot to land on!', '准备喂食', '在整个冬天（尤其是圣诞节前）喂养野生鸟类一直是斯堪的纳维亚半岛的一个传统。虽然主要目标是确保羽毛的朋友有足够的食物，以生存漫长的冬季几个月，鸟舍的创建服务于另一个目的，以及 - 让他们的创造者更仔细地看看他们的许多游客。正如你所看到的，当建立一个鸟类喂食器的唯一限制是你的想象力。例如，这组支线的拥有者显然预计未来几周的空中交通会非常拥挤。人们只能希望鸟儿不会觉得很难选择降落哪个地点！');
INSERT INTO "picture" VALUES (154, 20201205, 202012051600, 20201206, 'https://cn.bing.com', '/th?id=OHR.PLNP_ZH-CN8120863549_1920x1080.jpg&rf=LaDigue_1920x1080.jpg&pid=hp', '/th?id=OHR.PLNP_ZH-CN8120863549_UHD.jpg&rf=LaDigue_UHD.jpg&pid=hp', '/th?id=OHR.PLNP_ZH-CN8120863549', 'OHR.PLNP_ZH-CN8120863549_1920x1080.jpg', 'OHR.PLNP_ZH-CN8120863549_UHD.jpg', '普利特维采湖群国家公园中的高架步道，克罗地亚 (© Alessandro Laporta/Offset by Shutterstock)', 'Elevated path in Plitvice Lakes National Park, Croatia (© Alessandro Laporta/Offset by Shutterstock)', 'https://www.bing.com/search?q=Plitvice+Lakes+National+Park&form=hpcapt&filters=HpDate%3a%2220201206_0800%22', '', '/search?q=Bing+homepage+quiz&filters=WQOskey:%22HPQuiz_20201206_PLNP%22&FORM=HPQUIZ', 'true', 'f4aefccf9392203f45d7ff4fd7a09f83', 1, 1, 1, '[]', 'A hidden jewel in Croatia', 'Today we''re walking out into the winter wonderland of Plitvice Lakes National Park, the oldest and largest national park in Croatia. More than a million tourists per year flock to this central mountainous region, renowned for its cascading waterfalls and 16 turquoise-colored lakes. These wooden pathways meander for miles around and above the lakes, beside waterfalls and over streams and rivers, which disappear into the moss-covered earth only to burst through again somewhere downstream. In fact, the lakes are all interconnected by underground flows and are separated from each other by natural dams of travertine. The park is open year-round, and winter is its slowest season. If you''re brave enough to venture down the park''s slippery pathways in December or January, you may be rewarded with views straight out of a fairy tale.', '克罗地亚隐藏的宝石', '今天，我们将走进普里特维采湖国家公园的冬季仙境，这是克罗地亚最古老和最大的国家公园。每年超过一百万的游客涌向这个以瀑布和16个绿松石色湖泊而闻名的中部山区。这些木制小路蜿蜒数英里，在湖泊周围和上方，瀑布旁边，溪流和河流，消失在青苔覆盖的泥土中，但再次冲破下游某处。事实上，湖泊都是通过地下水流相互连接的，并且被天然的堤坝隔开。公园全年开放，冬季是最慢的季节。如果你有足够的勇气在12月或1月冒险沿着公园的湿滑小路，你可能会从童话故事中得到直接的景色。');
INSERT INTO "picture" VALUES (155, 20201204, 202012041600, 20201205, 'https://cn.bing.com', '/th?id=OHR.BenasqueValley_ZH-CN7931589735_1920x1080.jpg&rf=LaDigue_1920x1080.jpg&pid=hp', '/th?id=OHR.BenasqueValley_ZH-CN7931589735_UHD.jpg&rf=LaDigue_UHD.jpg&pid=hp', '/th?id=OHR.BenasqueValley_ZH-CN7931589735', 'OHR.BenasqueValley_ZH-CN7931589735_1920x1080.jpg', 'OHR.BenasqueValley_ZH-CN7931589735_UHD.jpg', '贝纳斯克，西班牙韦斯卡 (© Miscelleneoustock/Alamy)', 'The village of Benasque, Huesca, Spain (© Miscelleneoustock/Alamy)', 'https://www.bing.com/search?q=benasque+spain&form=hpcapt&filters=HpDate%3a%2220201205_0800%22', '', '/search?q=Bing+homepage+quiz&filters=WQOskey:%22HPQuiz_20201205_BenasqueValley%22&FORM=HPQUIZ', 'true', 'cbf201be3da0b16a00b15aa6aa200930', 1, 1, 1, '[]', 'A cozy winter village', 'When snow blankets the steep slopes of the Pyrenees—the mountain range that forms a natural border between Spain and France—the cozy Spanish village of Benasque offers a cheerful refuge on a winter''s eve. Beautifully preserved Romanesque and Renaissance manors and churches line the narrow cobblestone streets, and it''s easy to feel as though you''ve stepped back in time. Aside from these cultural charms, most visitors come to Benasque for outdoor adventure. Surrounded by the highest peaks of the Pyrenees, the Benasque Valley receives heavy snowfall and is a popular skiing destination. Summer attracts even more visitors to the area, when hiking, mountain biking, paragliding, and river rafting are big draws.', '舒适的冬季村庄', '当雪覆盖了比利牛斯山脉陡峭的山坡——西班牙和法国之间自然边界的山脉——舒适的西班牙贝纳斯克村在冬季前夕提供了一个欢快的避难所。保存完好的罗马式和文艺复兴时期的庄园和教堂在狭窄的鹅卵石街道上，很容易感觉你回到了过去。除了这些文化魅力，大多数游客来贝纳斯克户外冒险。贝纳斯克山谷被比利牛斯山脉最高的山峰所环绕，降雪量很大，是热门的滑雪胜地。夏季吸引更多游客到该地区，当徒步旅行，山地自行车，滑翔伞和河流漂流是大吸引。');
INSERT INTO "picture" VALUES (156, 20201203, 202012031600, 20201204, 'https://cn.bing.com', '/th?id=OHR.WCDBabyElephant_ZH-CN7844400740_1920x1080.jpg&rf=LaDigue_1920x1080.jpg&pid=hp', '/th?id=OHR.WCDBabyElephant_ZH-CN7844400740_UHD.jpg&rf=LaDigue_UHD.jpg&pid=hp', '/th?id=OHR.WCDBabyElephant_ZH-CN7844400740', 'OHR.WCDBabyElephant_ZH-CN7844400740_1920x1080.jpg', 'OHR.WCDBabyElephant_ZH-CN7844400740_UHD.jpg', '阿多大象国家公园中的非洲象，南非 (© Robert Harding/Alamy)', 'African elephants in Addo Elephant National Park in South Africa (© Robert Harding/Alamy)', 'https://www.bing.com/search?q=African+elephant&form=hpcapt&filters=HpDate%3a%2220201204_0800%22', '', '/search?q=Bing+homepage+quiz&filters=WQOskey:%22HPQuiz_20201204_WCDBabyElephant%22&FORM=HPQUIZ', 'true', '2cda6c427e885846bd4cd3fcc163a2a4', 1, 1, 1, '[]', 'Protecting wildlife today and tomorrow', 'For World Wildlife Conservation Day, we''re dropping in to visit a herd of African elephants in the Addo Elephant National Park in South Africa. Established in 1931 to protect a small herd of just 11 African elephants, today Addo ranks as the third-largest national park out of the 19 in South Africa and provides a safe haven for about 600 of these magnificent creatures, as well as cape buffaloes, various antelope species, lions, hyenas, and endangered black rhinos. The organizers of World Wildlife Conservation Day aim to raise awareness about the need to protect wildlife from illegal trafficking in animal parts and products. Because animal trafficking is the most immediate threat to wild elephants, tigers and rhinos, they encourage people to pledge to avoid products derived from wildlife. Consider the African elephant. Both subspecies—the African savannah elephant (like these) and the smaller African forest elephant—have long been targets of poachers for their ivory tusks. Although millions of elephants once roamed Africa, today only an estimated 400,000 remain.', '保护今天和明天的野生动物', '为了世界野生动物保护日，我们将来南非的阿多大象国家公园参观一群非洲象。成立于1931年，保护只有11头非洲大象的小群，如今阿多是南非19头大象中的第三大国家公园，为大约600只这些壮丽动物以及披风水牛、各种羚羊、狮子、土狼和濒危黑犀牛提供了安全避难所。世界野生动物保护日的组织者旨在提高人们对保护野生动物免受非法贩运动物零件和产品行为的认识。由于动物贩运是野生大象、老虎和犀牛最直接的威胁，因此它们鼓励人们承诺避免从野生动物中提取产品。以非洲象为名。这两个亚种——非洲大草原大象（像这样）和较小的非洲森林大象——长期以来都是偷猎者象牙象牙的目标。尽管数百万头大象曾经在非洲游荡，但今天估计只剩下40万头大象。');
INSERT INTO "picture" VALUES (157, 20201202, 202012021600, 20201203, 'https://cn.bing.com', '/th?id=OHR.BrasovXmas_ZH-CN2333670843_1920x1080.jpg&rf=LaDigue_1920x1080.jpg&pid=hp', '/th?id=OHR.BrasovXmas_ZH-CN2333670843_UHD.jpg&rf=LaDigue_UHD.jpg&pid=hp', '/th?id=OHR.BrasovXmas_ZH-CN2333670843', 'OHR.BrasovXmas_ZH-CN2333670843_1920x1080.jpg', 'OHR.BrasovXmas_ZH-CN2333670843_UHD.jpg', '布拉索夫中央广场的圣诞市集，罗马尼亚 (© Alpineguide/Alamy)', 'Christmas Market in Main Square of Braşov, Romania (© Alpineguide/Alamy)', 'https://www.bing.com/search?q=christmas+markets&form=hpcapt&filters=HpDate%3a%2220201203_0800%22', '', '/search?q=Bing+homepage+quiz&filters=WQOskey:%22HPQuiz_20201203_BrasovXmas%22&FORM=HPQUIZ', 'true', '7351c20aadfabada4982fec51907716e', 1, 1, 1, '[]', 'A Carpathian Christmas celebration', 'Nestled at the foot of Mount Tampa in the southern Carpathian Mountains of Romania, Brașov is a wonderful example of medieval Europe''s intersecting cultures. Founded by Teutonic Knights, settled by Saxons and Hungarians, influenced by the Ottoman Empire, the Tartars, and the native Romanians, the city''s Gothic architecture and unique cuisine reflect its rich history. The city''s Christmas market is held throughout the month of December and is dominated by a 90-foot-tall, live Christmas tree. The market''s numerous stalls feature food, drink, and local crafts. The festival is known as ''Braşov—the city from the tales,'' perhaps because legend has it that this square is where the children of Hamelin emerged after being led away by the Pied Piper. However you arrive, it''s a magical place to drink a cup of cheer and toast to your Romanian hosts with a hearty ''Noroc!'' But even if you''re keeping it local this year, it''s easy to be warmed even by the image of this golden glow from ''the city from the tales.''', '卡巴鄂圣诞庆典', '布拉索夫坐落在罗马尼亚南部可这辆车山脉的坦帕山脚下，是中世纪欧洲交汇文化的精彩例子。这座城市由Teutonic骑士团创建，由撒克逊人和匈牙利人定居，受奥斯曼帝国、塔塔尔人和罗马尼亚本地人的影响，这座城市的哥特式建筑和独特的美食反映了其丰富的历史。该市的圣诞市场在12月份举行，由一棵90英尺高的活圣诞树占据一半。市场的众多摊位以食品、饮料和当地工艺品为特色。这个节日被称为"布拉索夫——故事中的城市"，也许是因为传说这个广场是哈梅林的孩子们在被皮德派珀领走后出现的地方。无论你到达，这是一个神奇的地方，喝杯欢呼和吐司你的罗马尼亚主机与一个丰盛的''诺罗克！但是，即使你今年保持本地，它很容易被温暖，即使从"城市从故事中的城市"的金光闪闪的形象。');
INSERT INTO "picture" VALUES (158, 20201201, 202012011600, 20201202, 'https://cn.bing.com', '/th?id=OHR.PorcupineBay_ZH-CN2252758146_1920x1080.jpg&rf=LaDigue_1920x1080.jpg&pid=hp', '/th?id=OHR.PorcupineBay_ZH-CN2252758146_UHD.jpg&rf=LaDigue_UHD.jpg&pid=hp', '/th?id=OHR.PorcupineBay_ZH-CN2252758146', 'OHR.PorcupineBay_ZH-CN2252758146_1920x1080.jpg', 'OHR.PorcupineBay_ZH-CN2252758146_UHD.jpg', '基奈峡湾国家公园的尖顶湾，阿拉斯加 (© Sekar B/Shutterstock)', 'Cove of Spires in Kenai Fjords National Park, Alaska (© Sekar B/Shutterstock)', 'https://www.bing.com/search?q=alaska+national+interest+lands+conservation+act&form=hpcapt&filters=HpDate%3a%2220201202_0800%22', '', '/search?q=Bing+homepage+quiz&filters=WQOskey:%22HPQuiz_20201202_PorcupineBay%22&FORM=HPQUIZ', 'true', '4b729291a1259dbc3355d68efe6de423', 1, 1, 1, '[]', 'Protecting Alaska', 'On this day in 1980, President Jimmy Carter signed into law the Alaska National Interest Lands Conservation Act, which converted massive tracts of Alaskan wilderness into protected land. That single act 40 years ago doubled the size of the entire national park system. Alaska''s eight national parks cover more than 54 million acres. The Cove of Spires, shown here, is just one of the dramatic glacial landscapes that you can experience in Kenai Fjords National Park. Located near Seward, Alaska, the park is home to 38 glaciers which cover over half the park''s area in ice—though climate change has reduced that drastically over the last decades.', '保护阿拉斯加', '1980年的这一天，吉米·卡特总统签署了《阿拉斯加国家利益土地保护法》，将阿拉斯加大片荒野变成了受保护的土地。40年前的这一单一法案使整个国家公园系统的规模翻了一番。阿拉斯加的8个国家公园占地超过5400万英亩。这里展示的尖顶湾只是凯奈峡湾国家公园的戏剧性冰川景观之一。该公园位于阿拉斯加州塞沃德附近，拥有38座冰川，覆盖了公园一半以上的冰面，尽管在过去的几十年里，气候变化已经大大减少了这一点。');
INSERT INTO "picture" VALUES (159, 20201220, 202012201600, 20201221, 'https://cn.bing.com', '/th?id=OHR.CastleriggStone_ZH-CN8015482045_1920x1080.jpg&rf=LaDigue_1920x1080.jpg&pid=hp', '/th?id=OHR.CastleriggStone_ZH-CN8015482045_UHD.jpg&rf=LaDigue_UHD.jpg&pid=hp', '/th?id=OHR.CastleriggStone_ZH-CN8015482045', 'OHR.CastleriggStone_ZH-CN8015482045_1920x1080.jpg', 'OHR.CastleriggStone_ZH-CN8015482045_UHD.jpg', '凯西克附近的Castlerigg石圈，英国坎布里亚 (© Alan Copson/plainpicture)', 'Mountain goat kid in western Montana (© Donald M. Jones/Minden Pictures)', 'https://www.bing.com/search?q=mountain+goat&form=hpcapt&filters=HpDate%3a%2220201220_0800%22', '', '/search?q=Bing+homepage+quiz&filters=WQOskey:%22HPQuiz_20201220_BabyGoat%22&FORM=HPQUIZ', 'true', '6b1821c5e038b9ac0c59e730d4281a4c', 1, 1, 1, '[]', 'Dressed for winter fun', 'Native to North America, mountain goats live much of the year scaling peaks from southcentral Alaska down to the northern Rockies. They tend to live at high altitudes, often above 13,000 feet, where their sure-footed climbing ability allows them to clamber up extraordinarily steep, rocky slopes. In the winter, they''ll migrate down to slightly lower elevations to seek shelter in subalpine forests with south-facing rocky ledges, where the sun and relentless winds keep ice to a minimum. Here, they forage for lichen, mosses, grasses, and other wintery greens. Their woolly, two-layered coats keep them toasty as temperatures dip, which is probably why even in the chill of western Montana this young mountain goat—or kid—appears to be having a ball. Enjoying winter is all about how you dress.', '穿着冬季乐趣', '山羊原产于北美，一年中的大半年都生活在从阿拉斯加中南部到北落基山脉的山峰上。他们往往生活在高海拔地区，通常超过13，000英尺，在那里他们肯定脚的攀爬能力，让他们爬上异常陡峭的岩石斜坡。在冬季，他们将迁移到略低的海拔高度，在亚高山森林中寻找避难所，那里有朝南的岩石窗台，那里的太阳和无情的风将冰最降。在这里，他们为地衣、青苔、草和其他冬青植物而四食。他们的羊毛，双层外套让他们烤面包，因为温度下降，这大概就是为什么即使在蒙大拿州西部的寒冷，这只年轻的山羊-或孩子-似乎有一个球。享受冬天就是你穿得怎么样。');
INSERT INTO "picture" VALUES (160, 20201219, 202012191600, 20201220, 'https://cn.bing.com', '/th?id=OHR.BabyGoat_ZH-CN7863798344_1920x1080.jpg&rf=LaDigue_1920x1080.jpg&pid=hp', '/th?id=OHR.BabyGoat_ZH-CN7863798344_UHD.jpg&rf=LaDigue_UHD.jpg&pid=hp', '/th?id=OHR.BabyGoat_ZH-CN7863798344', 'OHR.BabyGoat_ZH-CN7863798344_1920x1080.jpg', 'OHR.BabyGoat_ZH-CN7863798344_UHD.jpg', '蒙大拿州西部的小雪羊 (© Donald M. Jones/Minden Pictures)', 'Early morning frost on trees in Mount Siguniang National Park in Sichuan Province, China (© Robert Harding World Imagery/Offset by Shutterstock)', 'https://www.bing.com/search?q=mount+siguniang+national+park&form=hpcapt&filters=HpDate%3a%2220201219_0800%22', '', '/search?q=Bing+homepage+quiz&filters=WQOskey:%22HPQuiz_20201219_Siguniangshan%22&FORM=HPQUIZ', 'true', 'c85b9f29a6dbdd03b996b1be2d03e148', 1, 1, 1, '[]', 'Four Sisters, thousands of trees', 'You''ll find this wintery, sylvan scene on the slopes of Mount Siguniang, the tallest summit of the Qionglai Mountains in Western China. Its name, which translates as ''Four Sisters Mountain,'' is inspired by the local Tibetan legend behind its four distinct peaks. According to the story, four sisters saved their people using a magic mirror to turn themselves into the mountain to imprison the devil. The tallest peak, peak of ''the youngest sister,'' stands at 20,500 feet and is an extremely challenging climb– it''s rarely attempted and wasn''t summitted until 1981. The surrounding park includes three valleys flanking the mountain and is part of the Sichuan Giant Panda Sanctuaries, a UNESCO World Heritage Site. In addition to giant pandas, the sanctuary is home to the red panda, the snow leopard, the clouded leopard, and between 5,000 and 6,000 species of plants.', '四姐妹，千树', '在中国西部琼莱山脉最高的山峰——西古尼昂山的山坡上，您会发现这个冬天的西尔万场景。它的名字，翻译为"四姐妹山"，灵感来自当地藏族传说背后的四个独特的山峰。根据这个故事，四个姐妹用一面魔镜拯救了他们的人民，把自己变成山来囚禁魔鬼。最高的山峰，"最小的妹妹"的山峰，高20，500英尺，是一个极具挑战性的攀登-它很少尝试，直到1981年才登顶。周围的公园包括三个山谷，两侧是山的两侧，是四川大熊猫保护区的一部分，被联合国教科文组织列为世界遗产。除了大熊猫，保护区是小熊猫，雪豹，云豹的家园，以及5000至6000种植物。');
INSERT INTO "picture" VALUES (161, 20201218, 202012181600, 20201219, 'https://cn.bing.com', '/th?id=OHR.Siguniangshan_ZH-CN7772066391_1920x1080.jpg&rf=LaDigue_1920x1080.jpg&pid=hp', '/th?id=OHR.Siguniangshan_ZH-CN7772066391_UHD.jpg&rf=LaDigue_UHD.jpg&pid=hp', '/th?id=OHR.Siguniangshan_ZH-CN7772066391', 'OHR.Siguniangshan_ZH-CN7772066391_1920x1080.jpg', 'OHR.Siguniangshan_ZH-CN7772066391_UHD.jpg', '清晨结了霜的树林，中国四姑娘山 (© Robert Harding World Imagery/Offset by Shutterstock)', 'Tre Cime di Lavaredo as seen from the Lavaredo fork, Sexten Dolomites, Italy (© AWL Images/Danita Delimont)', 'https://www.bing.com/search?q=tre+cime+di+lavaredo&form=hpcapt&filters=HpDate%3a%2220201218_0800%22', '', '/search?q=Bing+homepage+quiz&filters=WQOskey:%22HPQuiz_20201218_TreCime%22&FORM=HPQUIZ', 'true', '31790d6d76d63b94b60ce4a0ce172f83', 1, 1, 1, '[]', 'Where are the ''Pale Mountains''?', 'Behold the Tre Cime di Lavaredo, some of the most iconic peaks of the Dolomites range in the Italian Alps. The Dolomites, aka the ''Pale Mountains,'' are named for the light-colored stone (dolomite) of the jagged range. This is the view from the highest point of a trail that encircles these three dramatic peaks. Usually mobbed with tourists in the summertime, autumn and spring offer a chance for a more tranquil amble along the 6-mile trail. The hike manages to reveal one stunning view after another with each turn of the route. Along the way, the hiker will pass three ''rifugios,'' traditional Alpine shelters that offer drinks and meals, and even beds to stay the night. Until 1919, the border between Italy and Austria-Hungary ran directly through the Tre Cime di Lavaredo, and there was heavy fighting here in World War I. Visitors can still see trenches and remnants of fortifications left from the so-called White War of the Alps. A small chapel, called Cappella degli Alpini, was built in memory of fallen soldiers in the area.', '"帕莱山"在哪里？', '看看意大利阿尔卑斯山多洛米蒂山脉的一些最具标志性的山峰。多洛米蒂人，又名"帕莱山"，以锯齿状山脉的浅色石头（白云石）命名。这是从环绕这三个戏剧性山峰的小径的最高点看风景。通常在夏季、秋季和春季与游客一起围攻，为沿着 6 英里长的小径提供更宁静的宁静氛围。徒步旅行设法揭示一个又一个令人惊叹的景色，每次路线的转弯。一路上，徒步旅行者将经过三个"里夫吉奥斯"，传统的阿尔卑斯山庇护所，提供饮料和膳食，甚至床过夜。直到1919年，意大利和奥地利-匈牙利之间的边界直接穿过拉瓦拉雷多，在第一次世界大战中这里战火重重，游客仍然可以看到所谓的阿尔卑斯山白战争遗留下来的战壕和防御工事的遗迹。一座小教堂，叫做卡佩拉·德格利·阿尔皮尼，是为纪念该地区阵亡士兵而建的。');
INSERT INTO "picture" VALUES (162, 20201217, 202012171600, 20201218, 'https://cn.bing.com', '/th?id=OHR.TreCime_ZH-CN7609469681_1920x1080.jpg&rf=LaDigue_1920x1080.jpg&pid=hp', '/th?id=OHR.TreCime_ZH-CN7609469681_UHD.jpg&rf=LaDigue_UHD.jpg&pid=hp', '/th?id=OHR.TreCime_ZH-CN7609469681', 'OHR.TreCime_ZH-CN7609469681_1920x1080.jpg', 'OHR.TreCime_ZH-CN7609469681_UHD.jpg', '从环绕山峰的小径最高点看到的拉瓦莱多三峰山，意大利 (© AWL Images/Danita Delimont)', 'The English National Ballet''s 2016 production of ''The Nutcracker'' at the London Coliseum in London, England (© Robbie Jack/Corbis via Getty Images)', 'https://www.bing.com/search?q=the+nutcracker+ballet&form=hpcapt&filters=HpDate%3a%2220201217_0800%22', '', '/search?q=Bing+homepage+quiz&filters=WQOskey:%22HPQuiz_20201217_ENBNutcracker%22&FORM=HPQUIZ', 'true', '6eb44f06c90c0ea7eaf67d3103459460', 1, 1, 1, '[]', 'A holiday tradition endures', 'If it''s December, then countless ballet companies must be performing ''The Nutcracker.'' The ballet has become an iconic holiday entertainment staple, produced around the world. This photo captures a scene from the 2016 production by the English National Ballet at the London Coliseum. The company has been performing ''The Nutcracker'' there for 20 years. And despite the pandemic, they''ll be back at the Coliseum again this year, leaping and twirling to the ''Dance of the Sugar Plum Fairy,'' but in an abbreviated program before a reduced, physically distanced crowd. It''s perhaps the world''s most indomitable ballet today, but when ''The Nutcracker'' premiered on December 18, 1892, in St. Petersburg, Russia, it was far from a hit. Some critics appreciated Tchaikovsky''s score, but most found the choreography and dancing ''amateurish'' and ''insipid.'' Largely forgotten by the early 20th century, ''The Nutcracker'' made its US debut with a performance by the San Francisco Ballet company in 1944. It became a true Christmastime classic when choreographer George Balanchine staged his own 1954 production with the New York City Ballet. Balanchine''s version caught on and inspired other dance companies to perform it themselves. Most years, ''The Nutcracker'' is such a draw that a staging of Tchaikovsky''s Christmas fantasy can help keep a ballet company financially stable. Even in 2020, with all its challenges for the performing arts, ballet companies are doing what they can to keep this seasonal stalwart alive.', '节日传统经久不衰', '如果是12月，那么无数的芭蕾舞团一定在表演《胡桃夹子》。芭蕾已成为一个标志性的节日娱乐主食，在世界各地生产。这张照片拍摄了英国国家芭蕾舞团在伦敦体育馆2016年制作的一幕。该公司已经在那里表演了20年的"胡桃夹子"。尽管大流行，他们今年将再次回到体育馆，跳跃和旋转到"糖梅仙子的舞蹈"，但在一个缩写节目之前，减少，身体距离的人群。这也许是今天世界上最不屈不挠的芭蕾舞剧，但当《胡桃夹子》于1892年12月18日在俄罗斯圣彼得堡首映时，它远非一击。一些评论家欣赏柴可夫斯基的乐谱，但大多数人认为舞蹈和舞蹈是"业余的"和"平淡无奇的"。《胡桃夹子》在20世纪初被人们遗忘，1944年旧金山芭蕾舞团在美国首演。当编舞家乔治·巴兰钦在纽约市芭蕾舞团上演自己的1954年作品时，它成为了真正的圣诞经典。巴兰钦的版本抓住并启发了其他舞蹈公司自己表演。多数年，《胡桃夹子》如此吸引，柴可夫斯基的圣诞幻想舞台可以帮助保持芭蕾舞团的财务稳定。即使在2020年，尽管对表演艺术提出了所有挑战，但芭蕾舞团正在尽一切努力来保持这种季节性的坚强。');
INSERT INTO "picture" VALUES (163, 20201216, 202012161600, 20201217, 'https://cn.bing.com', '/th?id=OHR.NarniaForest_ZH-CN8466850438_1920x1080.jpg&rf=LaDigue_1920x1080.jpg&pid=hp', '/th?id=OHR.NarniaForest_ZH-CN8466850438_UHD.jpg&rf=LaDigue_UHD.jpg&pid=hp', '/th?id=OHR.NarniaForest_ZH-CN8466850438', 'OHR.NarniaForest_ZH-CN8466850438_1920x1080.jpg', 'OHR.NarniaForest_ZH-CN8466850438_UHD.jpg', '日落时分被雪覆盖的挪威云杉林，德国图林根 (© Frank Sommariva/ImageBROKER/Offset by Shutterstock)', 'Ludwig van Beethoven sculptures and monument at the Münsterplatz, Bonn, Germany (© dpa/Alamy Live News)', 'https://www.bing.com/search?q=ludwig+van+beethoven&form=hpcapt&filters=HpDate%3a%2220201216_0800%22', '', '/search?q=Bing+homepage+quiz&filters=WQOskey:%22HPQuiz_20201216_Beethoven250%22&FORM=HPQUIZ', 'true', '898ee8788822099fc264b8cab8571cdd', 1, 1, 1, '[]', 'Beethoven''s 250th', 'German composer Ludwig van Beethoven created melodies and harmonies we instantly recognize, even in this entertainment-saturated 21st century. Overcoming childhood abuse, hearing loss, romantic rejection, and bouts of depression and alcoholism, Beethoven channeled his stormy emotions into music that compelled audiences to viscerally feel what he felt. In the process, he helped end the regimented Classical era and usher in the Romantic period, where even the most flawed artists were sovereign. This scene at Bonn''s Münsterplatz features the city''s enduring Beethoven Monument (at rear), seemingly swarmed by an additional 700 green- and gold-colored Beethoven statues. Created by German conceptual artist Ottmar Hörl, the colorful statues were placed in the square last year in the run-up to the composer''s birthday. Beethoven concerts and celebrations had been planned in Germany and around the world throughout 2020 in honor of this milestone anniversary. Most have been pushed to next year due to the coronavirus pandemic, but with a quick Bing video search for your favorite symphony or sonata, you can join the world in appreciating Beethoven''s radical creativity.', '贝多芬的第250次', '德国作曲家路德维希·范·贝多芬创作了旋律和和声，我们立刻认出来，即使在这个娱乐饱和的21世纪。贝多芬克服了童年的虐待、听力损失、浪漫的排斥以及抑郁和酗酒的一轮，将他的暴风不由多的情绪引导到音乐中，迫使观众内心感受到他的感受。在这个过程中，他帮助结束了古典时代，迎来了浪漫主义时期，即使是最有缺陷的艺术家也是主权的。波恩的明斯特广场的这一幕以这座城市持久的贝多芬纪念碑（后方）为特征，似乎还有700尊绿色和金色的贝多芬雕像。这些五颜六色的雕像由德国概念艺术家Ottmar Hürl创作，去年在作曲家生日前被放置在广场上。贝多芬音乐会和庆祝活动已计划在德国和世界各地在整个2020年，以纪念这一里程碑式周年纪念日。由于冠状病毒大流行，大多数被推到明年，但通过快速的必应视频搜索你最喜欢的交响乐或奏鸣曲，你可以与全世界一起欣赏贝多芬的激进创造力。');
INSERT INTO "picture" VALUES (164, 20201221, 202012211600, 20201222, 'https://cn.bing.com', '/th?id=OHR.HolidayNubble_ZH-CN8122183595_1920x1080.jpg&rf=LaDigue_1920x1080.jpg&pid=hp', '/th?id=OHR.HolidayNubble_ZH-CN8122183595_UHD.jpg&rf=LaDigue_UHD.jpg&pid=hp', '/th?id=OHR.HolidayNubble_ZH-CN8122183595', 'OHR.HolidayNubble_ZH-CN8122183595_1920x1080.jpg', 'OHR.HolidayNubble_ZH-CN8122183595_UHD.jpg', '涅迪克角灯塔上的节日彩灯，缅因州 (© Walter Bibikow/Alamy)', 'Castlerigg Stone Circle near Keswick, Lake District, Cumbria, United Kingdom (© Alan Copson/plainpicture)', 'https://www.bing.com/search?q=castlerigg+stone+circle+cumbria+winter+solstice&form=hpcapt&filters=HpDate%3a%2220201221_0800%22', '', '/search?q=Bing+homepage+quiz&filters=WQOskey:%22HPQuiz_20201221_CastleriggStone%22&FORM=HPQUIZ', 'true', '1ad743a2985585b82ee59a8600460328', 1, 1, 1, '[]', 'Older than Stonehenge?', 'Roughly 5,000 years ago, ancient inhabitants of the British Isles somehow dragged as many as 40 giant stones—the heaviest weighing an estimated 16 tons—onto this grassy plateau in what is now England''s Lake District National Park in Cumbria. They then grouped them into the stone circle at Castlerigg, seen here casting shadows from the low winter sun. Archeologists believe stone circles, were arranged to align with solar and lunar positions. They were used in elaborate rituals to celebrate occasions like today''s winter solstice, the shortest day (and longest night) of the year in the Northern Hemisphere. Castlerigg is believed to be one of the oldest of the approximately 1,300 stone circles in Britain. And while it''s not as well-known as Stonehenge—which was probably begun soon after Castlerigg—its panoramic views of the neighboring Blencathra, Helvellyn, and Skiddaw mountains make it one of the most scenic. Even today, Castlerigg draws winter solstice revelers who beat drums and participate in the magical festival of Yule, in which a log is burned to symbolize the return of heat and light to the sun. And for those of you lamenting the short, cold days of winter, you can take some comfort in knowing that after today the hours of daylight will steadily lengthen, and in six months we''ll have traded positions with the Southern Hemisphere and will enjoy long, warm days once again.', '比巨石阵还老？', '大约5000年前，不利群岛的古代居民在坎布里亚的英格兰湖区国家公园将多达40块巨型石头——最重的石头——重约16吨——拖到这个草丛丛中的高原上。然后，他们把它们分成卡斯里格的石圈，在这里看到从低落的冬日阳光中投射阴影。考古学家认为，石圈是安排与太阳和月球位置对齐的。它们被用在精心制作的仪式中来庆祝，比如今天的冬至，北半球一年中最短的一天（和最长的夜晚）。卡斯里格被认为是英国大约1300个石圈中最古老的石圈之一。虽然它不像巨石阵那样出名——巨石阵可能早在卡斯里格之后——但它对邻近的布伦卡特拉、赫尔韦林和斯基道山脉的全景使得它成为风景最优美的山峰之一。即使在今天，Castlerigg还吸引着冬至狂欢者，他们敲鼓，参加尤勒的神奇节日，在这个节日里，一个原木被焚烧，象征着热和光回归太阳。对于那些哀叹冬天短暂寒冷的日子的人，你可以感到些安慰，因为知道今天之后，白天的时间将稳步延长，六个月后，我们将与南半球交换头寸，并再次享受漫长而温暖的日子。');
INSERT INTO "picture" VALUES (165, 20201222, 202012221600, 20201223, 'https://cn.bing.com', '/th?id=OHR.BandedPipefish_ZH-CN8209616080_1920x1080.jpg&rf=LaDigue_1920x1080.jpg&pid=hp', '/th?id=OHR.BandedPipefish_ZH-CN8209616080_UHD.jpg&rf=LaDigue_UHD.jpg&pid=hp', '/th?id=OHR.BandedPipefish_ZH-CN8209616080', 'OHR.BandedPipefish_ZH-CN8209616080_1920x1080.jpg', 'OHR.BandedPipefish_ZH-CN8209616080_UHD.jpg', '莫阿尔博阿尔附近的带纹矛吻海龙，菲律宾 (© Jenna Szerlag/Alamy)', 'Sindhudurg Fort, Maharashtra, India (© MovingMaratha/Alamy)', 'https://www.bing.com/search?q=Sindhudurg+Fort&form=hpcapt&filters=HpDate%3a%2220201223_0800%22', '', '/search?q=Bing+homepage+quiz&filters=WQOskey:%22HPQuiz_20201223_SeaFort%22&FORM=HPQUIZ', 'true', '5c941b9849ff540531337d70a04d1df3', 1, 1, 1, '[]', 'A historical fort', 'Sindhudurg Fort is a historical fort that occupies an island in the Arabian Sea, just off the coast of Maharashtra in Western India. The fort was built by chhatrapati Shivaji Maharaj . The fortress lies on the shore of Malvan town of Sindhudurg District in the Konkan region of Maharashtra. It is a protected monument.', '历史堡垒', '信德堡是一座历史悠久的堡垒，位于阿拉伯海的一个岛屿上，位于印度西部马哈拉施特拉邦海岸附近。这座堡垒是由查特拉帕蒂·希瓦吉·马哈拉杰建造的。这座堡垒位于马哈拉施特拉邦康坎地区信德堡区马尔万镇的岸边。它是一座受保护的纪念碑。');
INSERT INTO "picture" VALUES (166, 20201223, 202012231600, 20201224, 'https://cn.bing.com', '/th?id=OHR.WildReindeer_ZH-CN8301029606_1920x1080.jpg&rf=LaDigue_1920x1080.jpg&pid=hp', '/th?id=OHR.WildReindeer_ZH-CN8301029606_UHD.jpg&rf=LaDigue_UHD.jpg&pid=hp', '/th?id=OHR.WildReindeer_ZH-CN8301029606', 'OHR.WildReindeer_ZH-CN8301029606_1920x1080.jpg', 'OHR.WildReindeer_ZH-CN8301029606_UHD.jpg', '挪威苔原上的北极光和野生驯鹿 (© Anton Petrus/Getty Images)', 'Northern lights and wild reindeer on the tundra in Norway (© Anton Petrus/Getty Images)', 'https://www.bing.com/search?q=reindeer&form=hpcapt&filters=HpDate%3a%2220201224_0800%22', '', '/search?q=Bing+homepage+quiz&filters=WQOskey:%22HPQuiz_20201224_WildReindeer%22&FORM=HPQUIZ', 'true', '17c0cd47ca7f8819457a6fcf2676ded3', 1, 1, 1, '[]', 'Hey, don''t you guys have somewhere to be?', 'Known in North America as caribou, reindeer are built to live in freezing Arctic regions like northern Norway, where this herd was photographed under the transfixing swirl of the aurora borealis, or northern lights. Reindeer have evolved unique features that help them thrive in these harsh environments. Their noses are adapted to warm the air they breathe before it enters their lungs, which helps maintain a steady body temperature even in the coldest of weather. And most of their bodies, including their hooves, are covered with thick, dense fur to keep them well insulated. In fact, they are more likely to overheat then freeze—so when they''re flying through the starry skies tonight, they''ll be feeling snugger than Santa Claus in his red velvet suit. Reindeer were introduced to Christmas lore in 1823 with the poem ''A Visit from St. Nicholas,'' also known as ''The Night Before Christmas.'' Written by Clement Clarke Moore, the verses paint a picture of a Santa Claus and his sleigh, driven by eight flying reindeer—Dasher, Dancer, Prancer, Vixen, Comet, Cupid, Donner, and Blitzen. In 1939, Rudolph was added to Santa''s squad when Robert L. May created a story about the red-nosed misfit for his employer, Montgomery Ward, as part of a Christmas promotion for the department store. The famous reindeer are often referred to as males in pop culture (except, maybe, Vixen?), but as the animals are typically depicted with their antlers intact, it is more likely the seasonal sleigh-pullers are female. This is because male reindeer shed their antlers at the end of the mating season in early December, while females sport their thinner antlers throughout the winter. (Castrated males follow an antler cycle that''s similar to female reindeer, but we don''t', '嘿，你们没有地方可去吗？', '在北美被称为驯鹿，驯鹿是为了生活在像挪威北部这样的冰冻的北极地区而建造的，在那里，这种群群被拍摄在北极光或北极光的旋转下。驯鹿已经进化出独特的特征，帮助他们在这些恶劣的环境中茁壮成长。他们的鼻子被调整为在空气进入肺部之前加热呼吸的空气，这有助于即使在最寒冷的天气中保持稳定的体温。他们的身体，包括他们的蹄子，都覆盖着厚厚的，浓密的毛皮，以保持他们良好的绝缘。事实上，他们更可能过热，然后结冰——所以当他们今晚飞过星空时，他们会比穿着红色天鹅绒套装的圣诞老人感到更舒适。驯鹿在1823年被介绍给圣诞传说，诗"圣尼古拉斯的访问"，也被称为"圣诞节前夜"。这些诗句由克莱门特·克拉克·摩尔（Clement Clarke Moore）写成，描绘了一幅圣诞老人和他的雪橇，由八只飞行驯鹿——达舍、舞者、普朗瑟、维森、彗星、丘比特、唐纳和闪电战——驾驶。1939年，鲁道夫加入圣诞老人的队伍，当时罗伯特·梅（Robert L. May）为他的雇主蒙哥马利·沃德（Montgomery Ward）创作了一个关于红鼻子不合时宜的故事，作为百货公司圣诞促销活动的一部分。著名的驯鹿在流行文化中通常被称为雄性（也许，Vixen？这是因为雄性驯鹿在12月初的交配季节结束时脱落鹿角，而雌性驯鹿则在整个冬季运动其较薄的鹿角。（被割伤的雄性遵循鹿角周期， 类似于雌性驯鹿， 但我们不');
INSERT INTO "picture" VALUES (167, 20201224, 202012241600, 20201225, 'https://cn.bing.com', '/th?id=OHR.FRbluebirds_ZH-CN3972483010_1920x1080.jpg&rf=LaDigue_1920x1080.jpg&pid=hp', '/th?id=OHR.FRbluebirds_ZH-CN3972483010_UHD.jpg&rf=LaDigue_UHD.jpg&pid=hp', '/th?id=OHR.FRbluebirds_ZH-CN3972483010', 'OHR.FRbluebirds_ZH-CN3972483010_1920x1080.jpg', 'OHR.FRbluebirds_ZH-CN3972483010_UHD.jpg', '雪中的蓝山雀和大山雀，法国北孚日地区自然公园 (© Michel Rauch/Minden Pictures)', 'Santa''s giant sleigh and mailbox, Ilulissat, Greenland (© Walter Bibikow/Jon Arnold Images Ltd/Alamy)', 'https://www.bing.com/search?q=christmas&form=hpcapt&filters=HpDate%3a%2220201225_0800%22', '', '/search?q=Bing+homepage+quiz&filters=WQOskey:%22HPQuiz_20201225_SleighMailbox%22&FORM=HPQUIZ', 'true', 'c05d79b9e579f214aecaba18435a887b', 1, 1, 1, '[]', 'Big dreams require a big sleigh', 'For Christmas Day, we traveled 217 miles north of the Arctic Circle to Ilulissat, Greenland. It''s the island''s third-largest city, though in almost any other region, it would be considered a small town—only 4,670 people live here. Until a few years ago, Ilulissat served as a key destination for that most important holiday correspondence: Thousands of letters sent from around the world to Santa Claus, North Pole, ended up being rerouted to this giant mailbox. Today the mailbox has moved farther north, to Uummannaq, ever closer to the jolly old elf''s magical domicile. If you''re celebrating Christmas today, we hope you have a merry one.', '大梦需要大雪橇', '圣诞节那天，我们沿着北极圈以北217英里前往格陵兰岛的伊卢利萨特。它是该岛的第三大城市，尽管在几乎任何其他地区，它都会被视为一个小镇——只有4，670人住在这里。直到几年前，Ilulissat还是最重要的节日信件的主要目的地：从世界各地寄来数千封寄给北极圣诞老人的信件最终被改道到这个巨大的邮箱。今天，邮箱已经移动到更远的北方，到Uummannaq，越来越接近快乐的老精灵的神奇住所。如果你今天要庆祝圣诞节，我们希望你有一个快乐的。');
INSERT INTO "picture" VALUES (168, 20201227, 202012271600, 20201228, 'https://cn.bing.com', '/th?id=OHR.CanadaLynx_ZH-CN8645816958_1920x1080.jpg&rf=LaDigue_1920x1080.jpg&pid=hp', '/th?id=OHR.CanadaLynx_ZH-CN8645816958_UHD.jpg&rf=LaDigue_UHD.jpg&pid=hp', '/th?id=OHR.CanadaLynx_ZH-CN8645816958', 'OHR.CanadaLynx_ZH-CN8645816958_1920x1080.jpg', 'OHR.CanadaLynx_ZH-CN8645816958_UHD.jpg', '加拿大猞猁，蒙大拿州 (© Alan and Sandy Carey/Minden Pictures)', 'Nabana no Sato garden at night in Kuwana, Japan (© Zoonar GmbH/Alamy)', 'https://www.bing.com/search?q=nabana+no+sato+winter+light+festival&form=hpcapt&filters=HpDate%3a%2220201227_0800%22', '', '/search?q=Bing+homepage+quiz&filters=WQOskey:%22HPQuiz_20201227_NabananoSato%22&FORM=HPQUIZ', 'true', '9213805c3f0f6bbebd73215c10cc3396', 1, 1, 1, '[]', 'Turning darkness into light', 'Winter illuminations are a big deal in Japan and there is perhaps no bigger display than the one here at Nabana no Sato, a flower park in the gardens of Nagashima Spa Land in Kuwana, Japan. This image is just a glimpse of what awaits you in the park. More than 8.5 million LED lightbulbs illuminate pathways, trees, and the park''s famous ''Tunnel of Lights.'' While many of Japan''s light displays end after the new year, this one lasts from mid-October through early May.', '把黑暗变成光明', '冬季照明在日本是一个大问题，也许没有比这里的Nanana no Sato，一个位于日本库瓦纳的长岛温泉乐园的花卉公园的大展示。这张图片只是在公园里等待你的一瞥。超过850万个LED灯泡照亮了道路、树木和公园著名的"光之隧道"。虽然许多日本的灯光在新年结束后结束，但这个灯展从10月中旬一直到5月初。');
INSERT INTO "picture" VALUES (169, 20201226, 202012261600, 20201227, 'https://cn.bing.com', '/th?id=OHR.IbonPlan_ZH-CN8564017247_1920x1080.jpg&rf=LaDigue_1920x1080.jpg&pid=hp', '/th?id=OHR.IbonPlan_ZH-CN8564017247_UHD.jpg&rf=LaDigue_UHD.jpg&pid=hp', '/th?id=OHR.IbonPlan_ZH-CN8564017247', 'OHR.IbonPlan_ZH-CN8564017247_1920x1080.jpg', 'OHR.IbonPlan_ZH-CN8564017247_UHD.jpg', '比利牛斯山脉中的高山湖Ibón de Plan，西班牙韦斯卡 (© Getty Images)', 'Families play on the snow-covered slopes at Barnett Demesne Park, Belfast, Northern Ireland (© Stephen Barnes/Alamy)', 'https://www.bing.com/search?q=boxing+day&form=hpcapt&filters=HpDate%3a%2220201226_0800%22', '', '/search?q=Bing+homepage+quiz&filters=WQOskey:%22HPQuiz_20201226_BarnettsDemesne%22&FORM=HPQUIZ', 'true', '1c188e63e56e5409fc117089c00cd877', 1, 1, 1, '[]', 'Happy Boxing Day!', 'That ''Boxing Day (UK)'' printed on your calendar''s December 26 square has nothing to do with the sport of boxing—although for many modern Brits, Aussies, and other denizens of the Commonwealth, the holiday''s full slate of TV sporting events is the main observance. Folks with enough post-holiday energy might even slide down the hills at the grounds of this historic estate-turned public park, Barnett Demesne, in Belfast. But in older traditions, December 26 was the day nobles and other property owners offered gifts to servants and employees. It''s not clear if ''boxing'' refers to the boxes that held these presents, or to donation boxes customarily set up for the poor on the holiday—nor if these were so much gifts as reminders of one''s place on the feudal social ladder. But at any rate, as you shop those big sales and munch those tasty leftovers today, consider paying homage to Boxing Day''s origins by doing a good turn for someone down on their luck.', '节礼日快乐！', '12月26日，日历上印有"节礼日（英国）"与拳击运动没有任何关系——尽管对于许多现代英国人、澳大利亚人和英联邦其他居民来说，这个节日的全部电视体育赛事是主要的纪念活动。拥有足够假期后能量的人甚至可能从贝尔法斯特这个历史悠久的庄园变成公共公园的场地上滑下山。但在古老的传统中，12月26日是贵族和其他财产所有者向仆人和雇员赠送礼物的日子。不清楚"拳击"是指这些礼物的盒子，还是习惯在节日为穷人准备的捐赠箱，也不清楚这些礼物是否这么多，提醒人们注意自己在封建社会阶梯上的位置。但无论如何，当你购买那些大销售和咀嚼那些美味的剩菜今天，考虑致敬节礼日的起源，为某人做一个很好的转折，他们的运气下降。');
INSERT INTO "picture" VALUES (170, 20201225, 202012251600, 20201226, 'https://cn.bing.com', '/th?id=OHR.BarnettsDemesne_ZH-CN8484261440_1920x1080.jpg&rf=LaDigue_1920x1080.jpg&pid=hp', '/th?id=OHR.BarnettsDemesne_ZH-CN8484261440_UHD.jpg&rf=LaDigue_UHD.jpg&pid=hp', '/th?id=OHR.BarnettsDemesne_ZH-CN8484261440', 'OHR.BarnettsDemesne_ZH-CN8484261440_1920x1080.jpg', 'OHR.BarnettsDemesne_ZH-CN8484261440_UHD.jpg', 'Barnett Demesne公园中在白雪覆盖的山坡上玩耍的一家，北爱尔兰贝尔法斯特 (© Stephen Barnes/Alamy)', 'Santa''s giant sleigh and mailbox, Ilulissat, Greenland (© Walter Bibikow/Jon Arnold Images Ltd/Alamy)', 'https://www.bing.com/search?q=christmas&form=hpcapt&filters=HpDate%3a%2220201225_0800%22', '', '/search?q=Bing+homepage+quiz&filters=WQOskey:%22HPQuiz_20201225_SleighMailbox%22&FORM=HPQUIZ', 'true', '4303b7127fe4f3447084fb7e88814b06', 1, 1, 1, '[]', 'Big dreams require a big sleigh', 'For Christmas Day, we traveled 217 miles north of the Arctic Circle to Ilulissat, Greenland. It''s the island''s third-largest city, though in almost any other region, it would be considered a small town—only 4,670 people live here. Until a few years ago, Ilulissat served as a key destination for that most important holiday correspondence: Thousands of letters sent from around the world to Santa Claus, North Pole, ended up being rerouted to this giant mailbox. Today the mailbox has moved farther north, to Uummannaq, ever closer to the jolly old elf''s magical domicile. If you''re celebrating Christmas today, we hope you have a merry one.', '大梦需要大雪橇', '圣诞节那天，我们沿着北极圈以北217英里前往格陵兰岛的伊卢利萨特。它是该岛的第三大城市，尽管在几乎任何其他地区，它都会被视为一个小镇——只有4，670人住在这里。直到几年前，Ilulissat还是最重要的节日信件的主要目的地：从世界各地寄来数千封寄给北极圣诞老人的信件最终被改道到这个巨大的邮箱。今天，邮箱已经移动到更远的北方，到Uummannaq，越来越接近快乐的老精灵的神奇住所。如果你今天要庆祝圣诞节，我们希望你有一个快乐的。');
INSERT INTO "picture" VALUES (171, 20201228, 202012281600, 20201229, 'https://cn.bing.com', '/th?id=OHR.LucerneHoliday_ZH-CN8762232954_1920x1080.jpg&rf=LaDigue_1920x1080.jpg&pid=hp', '/th?id=OHR.LucerneHoliday_ZH-CN8762232954_UHD.jpg&rf=LaDigue_UHD.jpg&pid=hp', '/th?id=OHR.LucerneHoliday_ZH-CN8762232954', 'OHR.LucerneHoliday_ZH-CN8762232954_1920x1080.jpg', 'OHR.LucerneHoliday_ZH-CN8762232954_UHD.jpg', '卢塞恩老城，瑞士 (© Xantana/Getty Images)', 'Canada lynx in Montana (© Alan and Sandy Carey/Minden Pictures)', 'https://www.bing.com/search?q=canada+lynx&form=hpcapt&filters=HpDate%3a%2220201228_0800%22', '', '/search?q=Bing+homepage+quiz&filters=WQOskey:%22HPQuiz_20201228_CanadaLynx%22&FORM=HPQUIZ', 'true', '44b1f2bc4e6339482505bb21ca51494a', 1, 1, 1, '[]', 'Wildcat in a winter wonderland', 'If you''re lucky, you can catch a glimpse of this wily wildcat species in many places across Alaska and far-northern Canada. But here in Montana, a Canada lynx encounter like this is rare. While lynxes are known to live in cold climates from Washington state to Maine, they''ve been listed for two decades as threatened across the lower 48 states. This protective status under the Endangered Species Act—enacted on this day in 1973—aims to keep lynx and other animal populations healthy even in the face of climate change, habitat loss, and other threats to their survival. One success story: There''s now a stable lynx population far south of here in the Colorado Rockies, where the once-extirpated cats were reintroduced in 1999.', '冬天仙境中的野猫', '如果你幸运的话，你可以在阿拉斯加和加拿大北部的许多地方瞥见这种狡猾的野猫物种。但在蒙大拿州，这样的加拿大山猫遭遇是罕见的。众所周知，从华盛顿州到缅因州，山猫生活在寒冷的气候中，但20年来，它们一直被列为下48个州的威胁。1973年这一天颁布的《濒危物种法》的这一保护地位旨在保持山猫和其他动物种群的健康，即使面对气候变化、栖息地丧失和其他威胁，它们的生存。一个成功的故事：现在在科罗拉多落基山脉的南面有稳定的山猫种群，1999年，曾经被猫放养的猫被重新引进。');
INSERT INTO "picture" VALUES (172, 20201229, 202012291600, 20201230, 'https://cn.bing.com', '/th?id=OHR.WinterBryce_ZH-CN8874624326_1920x1080.jpg&rf=LaDigue_1920x1080.jpg&pid=hp', '/th?id=OHR.WinterBryce_ZH-CN8874624326_UHD.jpg&rf=LaDigue_UHD.jpg&pid=hp', '/th?id=OHR.WinterBryce_ZH-CN8874624326', 'OHR.WinterBryce_ZH-CN8874624326_1920x1080.jpg', 'OHR.WinterBryce_ZH-CN8874624326_UHD.jpg', '布莱斯峡谷国家公园的冬天，犹他州 (© Don Paulson/Danita Delimont)', 'Old town of Lucerne, Switzerland (© Xantana/Getty Images)', 'https://www.bing.com/search?q=old+town+of+lucerne+switzerland&form=hpcapt&filters=HpDate%3a%2220201229_0800%22', '', '/search?q=Bing+homepage+quiz&filters=WQOskey:%22HPQuiz_20201229_LucerneHoliday%22&FORM=HPQUIZ', 'true', '837c0a7c028cf2e704767647ad3583c2', 1, 1, 1, '[]', 'Where the glow of the holidays lingers', 'On the shores of Lake Lucerne and bestride the river Reuss, you''ll find the medieval Swiss city that shares the lake''s name. Emerging from a Benedictine monastery founded here in 750, Lucerne is today the largest town in central Switzerland. The central of three ancient, covered wooden pedestrian bridges of Lucerne''s Old Town has a unique feature. The interior of the Kapellbrücke (Chapel Bridge) is painted with religious scenes and allegories to edify those walking across it to the St. Peter''s Chapel. Though we are between holidays, the German-speaking city is just getting started. After Christmas and New Year''s Day, preparations begin for Fasnacht, the Swiss-German equivalent of Mardi Gras. Just like that carnival, the streets fill up with hundreds of fantastically masked and boisterous marchers, cutting loose before the fast of Lent.', '节日的光芒挥之不去', '在卢塞恩湖畔，在雷乌斯河畔，你会发现中世纪的瑞士城市，共享湖名。卢塞恩是瑞士中部最大的城镇，始建于750年，卢塞恩老城区三座古老的木制人行天桥的中心有其独特的特色。卡佩尔布吕克（查佩尔桥）的内部被涂上宗教场景和寓言，以教育那些穿过它到圣彼得教堂的人。虽然我们在假期之间，但德语城市才刚刚开始。圣诞节和新年之后，法斯纳赫特（Fasnacht）的筹备工作开始，法斯纳赫特是瑞士-德国相当于狂欢节的狂欢节。就像那个狂欢节一样，街上挤满了数百名蒙面和喧闹的游行者，在斋号前松了一口气。');
INSERT INTO "picture" VALUES (173, 20201230, 202012301600, 20201231, 'https://cn.bing.com', '/th?id=OHR.ZaragozaSpain_ZH-CN8995859415_1920x1080.jpg&rf=LaDigue_1920x1080.jpg&pid=hp', '/th?id=OHR.ZaragozaSpain_ZH-CN8995859415_UHD.jpg&rf=LaDigue_UHD.jpg&pid=hp', '/th?id=OHR.ZaragozaSpain_ZH-CN8995859415', 'OHR.ZaragozaSpain_ZH-CN8995859415_1920x1080.jpg', 'OHR.ZaragozaSpain_ZH-CN8995859415_UHD.jpg', '跨年庆典中燃放的烟花，西班牙萨拉戈萨 (© Martina Badini/Shutterstock)', 'Winter in Bryce Canyon National Park, Utah (© Don Paulson/Danita Delimont)', 'https://www.bing.com/search?q=bryce+canyon+national+park&form=hpcapt&filters=HpDate%3a%2220201230_0800%22', '', '/search?q=Bing+homepage+quiz&filters=WQOskey:%22HPQuiz_20201230_WinterBryce%22&FORM=HPQUIZ', 'true', 'eb60195369397ef5bc0bfb9da4266599', 1, 1, 1, '[]', 'Winter in the Wild West', 'When considering the dramatically eroded canyons of southwestern Utah, snow may not be the first thing that comes to mind. But far-flung Bryce Canyon National Park gets plenty of the white stuff, owing to its elevation of 8,000-plus feet at the massive amphitheater''s rim. The cold not only provides scenic snowy views and great cross-country skiing, it''s responsible for the striking red-rock pinnacles—known as hoodoos—that make the park so unique. High above sea level, winter in Bryce Canyon often sees daily shifts between freezing and above-freezing temperatures. Despite its name, Bryce Canyon isn''t a true canyon, but is instead a collection of natural amphitheaters. The park''s hoodoos formed as water seeped into massive stone plateaus, then froze and expanded to break away chunks of rock. Repeated day after day for eons, this process has left slim sections of sediment standing throughout Bryce Canyon—now the largest concentration of hoodoos in the world.', '狂野西部的冬天', '在考虑犹他州西南部被严重侵蚀的峡谷时，雪可能不是首先想到的。但遥远的布莱斯峡谷国家公园得到大量的白色的东西，因为它海拔8000多英尺的大型露天剧场的边缘。寒冷不仅提供风景秀丽的雪景和伟大的越野滑雪，它负责引人注目的红岩巅峰 - 被称为头巾 - 使公园如此独特。在海平面高，布莱斯峡谷的冬天经常看到每天在冰点和超过冰点的温度之间变化。尽管它的名字，布莱斯峡谷不是一个真正的峡谷，而是一个自然露天剧场的集合。当水渗入巨大的石高原时，公园的头巾形成，然后冻结并扩大，以打破大块的岩石。日复一日，这个过程已经留下整个布莱斯峡谷的泥沙的细小部分 -现在世界上最大的烟罩浓度。');
INSERT INTO "picture" VALUES (174, 20210103, 202101031600, 20210104, 'https://cn.bing.com', '/th?id=OHR.DiamondBeach_ZH-CN3165398805_1920x1080.jpg&rf=LaDigue_1920x1080.jpg&pid=hp', '/th?id=OHR.DiamondBeach_ZH-CN3165398805_UHD.jpg&rf=LaDigue_UHD.jpg&pid=hp', '/th?id=OHR.DiamondBeach_ZH-CN3165398805', 'OHR.DiamondBeach_ZH-CN3165398805_1920x1080.jpg', 'OHR.DiamondBeach_ZH-CN3165398805_UHD.jpg', '冰河湖对面的钻石冰沙滩，冰岛 (© surangaw/Getty Images)', 'Hohenschwangau Castle, Bavaria, Germany (© Mespilia/Shutterstock)', 'https://www.bing.com/search?q=hohenschwangau+castle&form=hpcapt&filters=HpDate%3a%2220210103_0800%22', '', '/search?q=Bing+homepage+quiz&filters=WQOskey:%22HPQuiz_20210103_HohenschwangauWinter%22&FORM=HPQUIZ', 'true', 'ab53e3c6060788e3f42cb1e01c769ada', 1, 1, 1, '[]', 'An Alpine fairytale castle', 'During a walking tour in the spring of 1829, Crown Prince (and future King) Maximilian II of Bavaria fell in love with these forested mountains and Alpine lakes, so three years later he bought the dilapidated remains of a 12th-century castle overlooking the village of Hohenschwangau. The yellow neo-Gothic castle that Maximilian built to replace the earlier ruins became the summer home and hunting retreat for the king, his wife Marie of Prussia, and their two sons, Ludwig and Otto. Hohenschwangau Castle became a kind of fantasy palace, particularly for the two young princes, who spent their time traipsing through the forest, reciting poetry, and staging scenes from the Romantic operas of Richard Wagner. After the death of King Maximilian in 1864, Ludwig ascended to the throne and moved into his father''s rooms in Hohenschwangau castle. He ordered that stars be painted onto the bedroom''s ceiling and had them illuminated by hidden oil lamps. Ludwig and his successors made few other modifications, so most of the rest of the castle remains unchanged even today—the 19th-century interiors contain period furniture, and preserved on the walls are more than 90 frescoes depicting heroic German folklore and the medieval legends of Wagner''s operas.', '阿尔卑斯山童话城堡', '在1829年春天的一次徒步旅行中，巴伐利亚的王储（和未来国王）马克西米利安二世爱上了这些森林覆盖的山脉和阿尔卑斯山湖泊，因此三年后，他买下了一座12世纪的城堡的破旧遗骸，俯瞰着霍恩施旺高村。马克西米利安为取代早期遗址而建造的黄色新哥特式城堡成为国王、普鲁士的妻子玛丽和他们的两个儿子路德维希和奥托的夏季家园和狩猎撤退地。霍恩施万高城堡成了一座梦幻宫殿，尤其是对两位年轻的王子来说，他们花时间在森林中穿山，背诵诗歌，并上演理查德·瓦格纳的浪漫歌剧场景。1864年马克西米利安国王去世后，路德维希登上王位，搬进了他父亲在霍恩施旺高城堡的房间。他命令把星星涂在卧室的天花板上，用隐藏的油灯照亮它们。路德维希和他的继任者几乎没有进行其他修改，因此城堡的其他大部分仍然保持不变——19世纪的室内装着时期的家具，墙壁上保存着90多幅壁画，描绘了德国英雄的民间传说和瓦格纳歌剧的中世纪传说。');
INSERT INTO "picture" VALUES (175, 20210102, 202101021600, 20210103, 'https://cn.bing.com', '/th?id=OHR.Goessweinstein_ZH-CN2155531895_1920x1080.jpg&rf=LaDigue_1920x1080.jpg&pid=hp', '/th?id=OHR.Goessweinstein_ZH-CN2155531895_UHD.jpg&rf=LaDigue_UHD.jpg&pid=hp', '/th?id=OHR.Goessweinstein_ZH-CN2155531895', 'OHR.Goessweinstein_ZH-CN2155531895_1920x1080.jpg', 'OHR.Goessweinstein_ZH-CN2155531895_UHD.jpg', '远眺格斯韦因斯泰因村和格斯韦因斯泰因城堡 (© Juergen Sack/Getty Images)', 'Sơn Đoòng cave in Phong Nha-Kẻ Bàng National Park, Vietnam (© David A Knight/Shutterstock)', 'https://www.bing.com/search?q=son+doong+cave&form=hpcapt&filters=HpDate%3a%2220210102_0800%22', '', '/search?q=Bing+homepage+quiz&filters=WQOskey:%22HPQuiz_20210102_LargestCave%22&FORM=HPQUIZ', 'true', 'c4fbaa4ec2bb0f49431c25d4a88994c1', 1, 1, 1, '[]', 'A universe underground', 'When Vietnamese farmer Hồ Khanh stumbled upon this cave in 1991, it was immediately clear the gaping mouth led to a huge, dark, untouched chamber, complete with a free-flowing underground river. What couldn''t have been clear to him then was that this cave, now known as Sơn Đoòng, is by far the world''s largest in volume. Lacking gear to explore the cave further, Khanh could only wander back home and tell friends about his discovery. But he was unable to retrace his steps to the cavern, his tracks engulfed by the jungle. Relegated to rumor, the cave went unexplored for almost two decades until a visiting team of British cavers caught wind of Khanh''s tale. In 2009, Khanh led them to Sơn Đoòng after a long search, and explorations commenced that found the cave was vast beyond anyone''s expectations. Sơn Đoòng is over 1.5 billion cubic feet in volume, with its main chamber 650 feet high, almost 500 feet wide, and stretching more than 3 miles, large enough to fly a Boeing 747 through—but look out for the 15-story stalagmites. One of the cave''s massive dolines—sunken, sun-exposed sections like the one seen here—hosts an entire rainforest ecosystem. And that''s just what we know so far: Cave divers have yet to fully explore Sơn Đoòng''s subterranean river, and vast passages found as recently as 2019 have only added to what''s known of the cave''s enormity.', '地下的宇宙', '1991年，当越南农民Hồ Khanh偶然发现这个洞穴时，它立刻被清理开得一片空白，导致一个巨大的，黑暗的，原封不动的室内，有一条自由流动的地下河流。当时他不可能清楚的是，这个洞穴，现在被称为Sơn\ü Sơn，是迄今为止世界上最大的体积。由于缺乏进一步探索洞穴的装备，Khanh只能漫步回家，告诉朋友他的发现。但他无法回溯他的脚步到洞穴，他的踪迹吞没了丛林。被辟谣，洞穴去探索了近20年，直到一个来访的英国洞穴队抓住了汗的故事风。2009年，Khanh带领他们Sơn一个3号，经过长时间的搜索，并开始了探索，发现洞穴是巨大的超出任何人的预期。Sơn 15 亿立方英尺的体积超过 15 亿立方英尺，主室高 650 英尺，宽近 500 英尺，绵延 3 英里以上，足以驾驶波音 747 飞过，但请小心 15 层的石笋。洞穴中一个巨大的多林——像这里看到的凹陷、阳光照射的部分——拥有整个雨林生态系统。而这就是我们目前所了解的：洞穴潜水员尚未充分探索Sơn年奥昂的地下河流，而2019年发现的大片通道只是增加了洞穴的浩瀚。');
INSERT INTO "picture" VALUES (176, 20210101, 202101011600, 20210102, 'https://cn.bing.com', '/th?id=OHR.LargestCave_ZH-CN2069899703_1920x1080.jpg&rf=LaDigue_1920x1080.jpg&pid=hp', '/th?id=OHR.LargestCave_ZH-CN2069899703_UHD.jpg&rf=LaDigue_UHD.jpg&pid=hp', '/th?id=OHR.LargestCave_ZH-CN2069899703', 'OHR.LargestCave_ZH-CN2069899703_1920x1080.jpg', 'OHR.LargestCave_ZH-CN2069899703_UHD.jpg', '峰牙－己榜国家公园中的韩松洞，越南 (© David A Knight/Shutterstock)', 'Polar bear in waters off Svalbard, Norway (© Westend61/Getty Images)', 'https://www.bing.com/search?q=new+year%27s+day&form=hpcapt&filters=HpDate%3a%2220210101_0800%22', '', '/search?q=Bing+homepage+quiz&filters=WQOskey:%22HPQuiz_20210101_LoonyDook%22&FORM=HPQUIZ', 'true', '6e67bbbc2fbd3d83ef513c71c201a31c', 1, 1, 1, '[]', 'Take the plunge into 2021', 'Happy New Year! Last year was pretty bracing and most of us are more than ready to start a new one. This polar bear seems to be shaking off 2020 with his own very own—and very authentic—polar bear plunge in the waters off the Svalbard archipelago way up in the Arctic Ocean. Though the earliest records of organized ice swimming come from Russia (naturally), the practice is now very widespread. All around the world, hardy souls will be starting the new year with their own dip into icy waters. For many, the plunge will raise money for charities, but cold-water swims have other benefits as well. Those healthy enough to do it and who have trained for it know that ice swimming has been shown to have some measurably positive health effects. Regular participants report less stress, fatigue, and chronic pain, as well as better memory function, mood, and energy levels. Or, you could just snuggle down deeper under the covers and sleep off last night''s excesses for a little bit longer and see if 2021 looks any better.', '冒险进入2021年', '新年快乐！去年是相当令人振奋的， 我们大多数人都准备开始一个新的。这只北极熊似乎正在摆脱2020年与他自己的-非常真实的-北极熊跳在斯瓦尔巴德群岛附近的水域的方式北冰洋。虽然有组织的冰上游泳最早的记录来自俄罗斯（自然），但这种做法现在非常普遍。在世界各地，坚强的灵魂将开始新的一年，他们自己浸入冰冷的水域。对许多人来说，跳水将为慈善机构筹集资金，但冷水游泳还有其他好处。那些健康到足以做到这一点，谁已经训练它知道，冰上游泳已被证明有一些可衡量的积极健康影响。定期参与者报告较少的压力、疲劳和慢性疼痛，以及更好的记忆功能、情绪和能量水平。或者， 你可以紧贴着更深的封面下， 睡一会儿昨晚的过度行为， 看看 2021 年看起来是否更好。');
INSERT INTO "picture" VALUES (177, 20201231, 202012311600, 20210101, 'https://cn.bing.com', '/th?id=OHR.LoonyDook_ZH-CN1879420705_1920x1080.jpg&rf=LaDigue_1920x1080.jpg&pid=hp', '/th?id=OHR.LoonyDook_ZH-CN1879420705_UHD.jpg&rf=LaDigue_UHD.jpg&pid=hp', '/th?id=OHR.LoonyDook_ZH-CN1879420705', 'OHR.LoonyDook_ZH-CN1879420705_1920x1080.jpg', 'OHR.LoonyDook_ZH-CN1879420705_UHD.jpg', '斯瓦尔巴群岛附近水域的北极熊，挪威 (© Westend61/Getty Images)', 'Fireworks during a New Year''s Eve celebration in Zaragoza, Spain (© Martina Badini/Shutterstock)', 'https://www.bing.com/search?q=new+years+eve&form=hpcapt&filters=HpDate%3a%2220201231_0800%22', '', '/search?q=Bing+homepage+quiz&filters=WQOskey:%22HPQuiz_20201231_ZaragozaSpain%22&FORM=HPQUIZ', 'true', '708498c78b14115b3ea843b555a89497', 1, 1, 1, '[]', 'Goodbye, 2020!', 'New Year''s Eve celebrations around the world will look a lot different this year, but as we ring in 2021 (and bid good riddance to 2020?) we can still enjoy this view of fireworks from a previous year in, Spain. The cathedral in the background is the Basílica de Nuestra Señora del Pilar, which was constructed over centuries beginning in 1681, though several churches had been built on the site prior to that. On the left is the Puente de Piedra Bridge, which spans the Ebro River. It''s also known as the Bridge of Lions because statues of lions (symbols of the city) stand at each end of the bridge. Zaragoza is famous for its landmarks and architecture, as well as for local cuisine, and seasonal festivals—which we can only hope return soon.', '再见， 2020 ！', '今年世界各地的除夕庆祝活动看起来会大不相同，但随着我们在2021年敲响警钟（以及申办到2020年？），我们仍然可以欣赏到西班牙去年的烟花。背景为大教堂，是1681年开始的几个世纪建造的新大教堂，但在此之前，该遗址上已经建造了几座教堂。左边是横跨埃布罗河的皮德拉大桥。它也被称为狮子桥，因为狮子雕像（城市的象征）站在桥的两端。萨拉戈萨以其地标和建筑，以及当地美食和季节性节日而闻名，我们只能希望很快回来。');
INSERT INTO "picture" VALUES (178, 20210104, 202101041600, 20210105, 'https://cn.bing.com', '/th?id=OHR.RedFrontMacaw_ZH-CN6432596112_1920x1080.jpg&rf=LaDigue_1920x1080.jpg&pid=hp', '/th?id=OHR.RedFrontMacaw_ZH-CN6432596112_UHD.jpg&rf=LaDigue_UHD.jpg&pid=hp', '/th?id=OHR.RedFrontMacaw_ZH-CN6432596112', 'OHR.RedFrontMacaw_ZH-CN6432596112_1920x1080.jpg', 'OHR.RedFrontMacaw_ZH-CN6432596112_UHD.jpg', '奥梅雷克的红额金刚鹦鹉，玻利维亚科恰班巴 (© Bernard Castelein/Minden Pictures)', 'Diamond Beach across from Jökulsárlón, a glacier lagoon in Iceland (© surangaw/Getty Images)', 'https://www.bing.com/search?q=j%C3%B6kuls%C3%A1rl%C3%B3n&form=hpcapt&filters=HpDate%3a%2220210104_0800%22', '', '/search?q=Bing+homepage+quiz&filters=WQOskey:%22HPQuiz_20210104_DiamondBeach%22&FORM=HPQUIZ', 'true', 'ea30e439d92fd6ebaccc0161cacb343a', 1, 1, 1, '[]', 'Sparkling ice diamonds on a black sandy beach', 'The icebergs stranded on this magnificent black sandy beach in Iceland are what give Diamond Beach its name. Sparkling like gems, they''re a natural museum of sorts for tourists who flock to this beach year-round to walk among the nature-made sculptures, with some icebergs as tall as the tourists themselves. It''s about a five-hour drive east from the capital of Reykjavik to get here. But the biggest attraction in this area is Jökulsárlón, the glacial lake just across the Ring Road from this beach. It''s a sparkling, still, blue lagoon dotted with huge glacial icebergs, which tourists motor around via pontoon boats. The lake began forming in 1934, when the Breiðamerkurjökull glacier started retreating, leaving the lagoon in its path. The lake''s size has increased fourfold since the 1970s.', '黑色沙滩上闪闪发光的冰钻石', '搁浅在冰岛这个宏伟的黑色沙滩上的冰山，让钻石海滩得名。像宝石一样闪闪发光，是一个自然的博物馆，游客们一年四生地涌向这个海滩，在自然制造的雕塑中漫步，有些冰山和游客一样高。从首都雷克雅未克向东驱车约5小时到达。但该地区最大的景点是Jükulsérlón，这个海滩对面的冰川湖。这是一个波光粼粼的，静止的，蓝色的泻湖点缀着巨大的冰川冰山，游客通过浮桥船四处航行。1934年，当布列亚默库尔冰川开始退却时，湖水开始形成，使泻湖在它的路径上。自20世纪70年代以来，这个湖的面积增加了四倍。');
INSERT INTO "picture" VALUES (179, 20210110, 202101101600, 20210111, 'https://cn.bing.com', '/th?id=OHR.SierraNevada_ZH-CN0564237735_1920x1080.jpg&rf=LaDigue_1920x1080.jpg&pid=hp', '/th?id=OHR.SierraNevada_ZH-CN0564237735_UHD.jpg&rf=LaDigue_UHD.jpg&pid=hp', '/th?id=OHR.SierraNevada_ZH-CN0564237735', 'OHR.SierraNevada_ZH-CN0564237735_1920x1080.jpg', 'OHR.SierraNevada_ZH-CN0564237735_UHD.jpg', 'Pradollano滑雪站，西班牙内华达山脉国家公园 (© NTCo/iStock/Getty Images Plus)', 'Huanglong Scenic and Historic Interest Area in Sichuan, China (© primeimages/Getty Images)', 'https://www.bing.com/search?q=huanglong+scenic+and+historic+interest+area&form=hpcapt&filters=HpDate%3a%2220210110_0800%22', '', '/search?q=Bing+homepage+quiz&filters=WQOskey:%22HPQuiz_20210110_GoldenDragon%22&FORM=HPQUIZ', 'true', '9ffe8630042e43a2192e8058313f6dc8', 1, 1, 1, '[]', 'China''s colorful terraced pools', 'While the sight of these gorgeous pools may make you want to don a swimsuit and plunge in for a refreshing soak, we don''t recommend it. The water may fed by underground geothermal springs, but these are no hot springs—the water''s only about 41 F. We''ll take it all in from dry land. Thee striking series of terraced, travertine pools cascade downward for nearly two miles. Formed over thousands of years, calcite deposits give the water its unique, and welcoming, turquoise coloration. Huanglong is officially called a Scenic and Historic Interest Area, and we can see why. There are plenty of other things to see and do at this huge park nestled between snow-capped peaks in central China''s Sichuan province. With abundant forests, lakes, and glaciers, the diverse mountain ecosystem is home to a rich variety of animals, including endangered giant pandas and golden snub-nosed monkeys. So extensive and breathtakingly beautiful is this landscape that roughly 200 square miles of it were designated a UNESCO World Heritage Site in 1992.', '中国五颜六色的梯田泳池', '虽然看到这些华丽的游泳池可能会让你想穿泳衣和跳进一个清爽的浸泡，我们不推荐它。水可能由地下地热泉提供，但这些不是温泉——水只有41华氏度。我们将从旱地全部拿走。引人注目的一系列梯田，三元池向下级联近两英里。钙化物矿床形成数千年来，使水具有其独特的、温馨的绿松石色色。黄龙被正式称为风景名胜和历史景区，我们明白为什么。在中国中部四川省的雪峰之间，这个巨大的公园还有很多其他值得一看的。丰富的森林、湖泊和冰川，是种类繁多的动物的家园，包括濒危大熊猫和金鼻猴。如此广泛和令人叹为观止的美丽是这个景观，它约200平方英里，它被指定为联合国教科文组织世界遗产在1992年。');
INSERT INTO "picture" VALUES (180, 20210109, 202101091600, 20210110, 'https://cn.bing.com', '/th?id=OHR.GoldenDragon_ZH-CN9908231664_1920x1080.jpg&rf=LaDigue_1920x1080.jpg&pid=hp', '/th?id=OHR.GoldenDragon_ZH-CN9908231664_UHD.jpg&rf=LaDigue_UHD.jpg&pid=hp', '/th?id=OHR.GoldenDragon_ZH-CN9908231664', 'OHR.GoldenDragon_ZH-CN9908231664_1920x1080.jpg', 'OHR.GoldenDragon_ZH-CN9908231664_UHD.jpg', '四川黄龙风景名胜区，中国 (© primeimages/Getty Images)', 'Spanish shawl nudibranch on kelp off Santa Catalina Island, Channel Islands, California (© WaterFrame/Alamy)', 'https://www.bing.com/search?q=spanish+shawl+nudibranch&form=hpcapt&filters=HpDate%3a%2220210109_0800%22', '', '/search?q=Bing+homepage+quiz&filters=WQOskey:%22HPQuiz_20210109_SpanishSeaSlug%22&FORM=HPQUIZ', 'true', '201e0c5692dd813578dc6c6f1e92d6e3', 1, 1, 1, '[]', 'One stylish slug', 'Today we''re meeting one of a motley group of sea slugs called the nudibranchs (rhymes with ''thanks''), known for their unique, often complex shapes and neon-bright colors that help discourage predators. The Spanish shawl''s fire-orange mane is made up of tendrils called cerata that mainly act as gills. But that mane also retains venom from the slug''s prey—sea anemones—treating any would-be devourers to a painful sting. Should a ravenous sea star disregard these defenses and get too close for comfort, the Spanish shawl has a Plan B: By flapping its whole 2- to 3-inch body like a gelatinous wing, the nudibranch can flutter into open water for a quick escape.', '一个时尚的 slug', '今天，我们会议了一群叫"感谢"的海鸥，它们以独特、通常复杂的形状和霓虹灯鲜艳的颜色而广为人知，有助于阻止捕食者。西班牙披肩的火橙毛是由肌腱称为塞拉塔，主要作为刺。但是，这种毛也保留了来自鱼的猎物——海葵——的毒液——它对待任何可能吞食的食鸟都会感到痛苦的刺痛。如果一个贪婪的海星无视这些防御，并得到太接近舒适，西班牙披肩有一个计划B：通过拍打其整个2至3英寸的身体像一个明胶翅膀，核支可以飘入开阔的水中快速逃脱。');
INSERT INTO "picture" VALUES (181, 20210108, 202101081600, 20210109, 'https://cn.bing.com', '/th?id=OHR.SpanishSeaSlug_ZH-CN9583688017_1920x1080.jpg&rf=LaDigue_1920x1080.jpg&pid=hp', '/th?id=OHR.SpanishSeaSlug_ZH-CN9583688017_UHD.jpg&rf=LaDigue_UHD.jpg&pid=hp', '/th?id=OHR.SpanishSeaSlug_ZH-CN9583688017', 'OHR.SpanishSeaSlug_ZH-CN9583688017_1920x1080.jpg', 'OHR.SpanishSeaSlug_ZH-CN9583688017_UHD.jpg', '圣卡塔利娜岛附近海藻上的西班牙披肩海蛞蝓，加利福尼亚海峡群岛 (© WaterFrame/Alamy)', 'Foucault pendulum at the Panthéon in Paris, France (© Adolf/Adobe Stock)', 'https://www.bing.com/search?q=foucault+pendulum+definition&FORM=hpcapt&filters=HpDate%3a%2220210108_0800%22', '', '/search?q=Bing+homepage+quiz&filters=WQOskey:%22HPQuiz_20210108_FoucaultsPendulum%22&FORM=HPQUIZ', 'true', '86f144c4e3629665246de1ec298238f9', 1, 1, 1, '[]', 'Take this for a spin...', 'In 1851, when French physicist Léon Foucault performed his pendulum experiment in Paris, he became the first to prove what many scientists of his day already suspected—that the Earth spins on an axis. He conducted his first experiments 170 years ago, in early January 1851, with a relatively small prototype in the cellar of his home. Just a month later, Foucault performed his most famous pendulum demonstration, using a 62-pound spherical weight attached to a 220-foot wire, which was hung from the dome of the Panthéon, a Parisian monument. As the pendulum swung back and forth in a fixed plane over a compass-like circle of sand below it, onlookers watched as the circle rotated. This in turn demonstrated that the Earth itself was rotating underneath it, and by extension, everyone watching was rotating as well, spinning on the surface of the great blue marble around its axis. All these years later, replicas of Foucault''s pendulum can still be found in museums around the world, continuing to demonstrate this elegant scientific proof. The pendulum seen here, an exact copy of the original, has been on display in Paris since 1995.', '拿这个来兜风...', '1851年，当法国物理学家莱昂·福柯在巴黎进行钟摆实验时，他成为第一个证明他当时许多科学家已经怀疑的——地球在轴上旋转的人。170年前的1851年1月初，他在家的地窖里用一个相对较小的原型进行了他的第一次实验。仅仅一个月后，福柯用一根220英尺长的电线上连接着62磅重的钟摆表演他最著名的钟摆，挂在巴黎纪念碑Panthéon的圆顶上。当钟摆在固定平面上来回摆动，在它下面的一个像指南针一样的沙子上时，旁观者看着圆旋转。这反过来又表明地球本身在它下面旋转，延伸，所有观看的人也都在旋转，围绕其轴线在巨大的蓝色大理石表面旋转。这些年过去了，福柯钟摆的复制品仍然可以在世界各地的博物馆找到，继续证明这个优雅的科学证据。这里看到的钟摆是原件的精确副本，自1995年以来一直在巴黎展出。');
INSERT INTO "picture" VALUES (182, 20210107, 202101071600, 20210108, 'https://cn.bing.com', '/th?id=OHR.FoucaultsPendulum_ZH-CN9435794626_1920x1080.jpg&rf=LaDigue_1920x1080.jpg&pid=hp', '/th?id=OHR.FoucaultsPendulum_ZH-CN9435794626_UHD.jpg&rf=LaDigue_UHD.jpg&pid=hp', '/th?id=OHR.FoucaultsPendulum_ZH-CN9435794626', 'OHR.FoucaultsPendulum_ZH-CN9435794626_1920x1080.jpg', 'OHR.FoucaultsPendulum_ZH-CN9435794626_UHD.jpg', '巴黎先贤祠内的傅科摆，法国 (© Adolf/Adobe Stock)', 'White Cliffs of Dover, England (© LisaValder/Getty Images)', 'https://www.bing.com/search?q=white+cliffs+of+dover&form=hpcapt&filters=HpDate%3a%2220210107_0800%22', '', '/search?q=Bing+homepage+quiz&filters=WQOskey:%22HPQuiz_20210107_WhiteCliffs%22&FORM=HPQUIZ', 'true', 'c8b195fa661cfaeb673cfdad30e78d35', 1, 1, 1, '[]', 'Of balloons and lost pantaloons', 'We all fly by the seat of our pants now and then, but how about flying with no pants at all? That was the plight of Jean-Pierre Blanchard and John Jeffries, who on January 7, 1785, made history over these chalk cliffs with the first aerial crossing of the English Channel. When their hydrogen-filled balloon dropped altitude due to overloading, the two tossed all the cargo they could into the drink below, britches included. Reaching France in their underpants, the undoubtedly chilly pilots still received a warm welcome. Known worldwide as an emblem of England, the White Cliffs of Dover rise 350 feet over the strait where Blanchard and Jeffries made their crossing. The white chalk and gray-black streaks of flint match geologically with shorter cliffs on the French side—evidence of a land bridge that existed long before we primates got the notion to fly. Of course, even soaring over the waves is a bit outmoded now that you can zip under them in the Channel Tunnel, which has its entrance just down the coast.', '气球和丢失的潘塔隆', '我们都在裤子的座位上飞来飞去， 但是没有裤子飞怎么样？这就是让-皮埃尔·布兰查德和约翰·杰弗里斯的困境，他们于1785年1月7日第一次穿越英吉利海峡，在这些粉笔悬崖上创造了历史。当他们的充满氢气的气球因超载而下降高度时，两人把所有可以装的货物都扔进了下面的饮料里，包括英国人。到达法国的内裤，毫无疑问寒冷的飞行员仍然受到热烈欢迎。众所周知，多佛的白崖被誉为英国的象征，在布兰查德和杰弗里斯的海峡上高高350英尺。白色粉笔和灰黑色的火石条纹在地质上与法国一侧的悬崖相配——这证明，早在我们灵长类动物得到飞行的概念之前，就已经存在了一座陆桥。当然，即使浪高飞过，现在也有点过时了，你可以在海峡隧道下拉链，隧道的入口就在海岸下。');
INSERT INTO "picture" VALUES (183, 20210106, 202101061600, 20210107, 'https://cn.bing.com', '/th?id=OHR.WhiteCliffs_ZH-CN9314988447_1920x1080.jpg&rf=LaDigue_1920x1080.jpg&pid=hp', '/th?id=OHR.WhiteCliffs_ZH-CN9314988447_UHD.jpg&rf=LaDigue_UHD.jpg&pid=hp', '/th?id=OHR.WhiteCliffs_ZH-CN9314988447', 'OHR.WhiteCliffs_ZH-CN9314988447_1920x1080.jpg', 'OHR.WhiteCliffs_ZH-CN9314988447_UHD.jpg', '多佛尔白崖，英国多佛尔 (© LisaValder/Getty Images)', 'Crater Lake in Oregon (© Steve Bloom Images/Alamy)', 'https://www.bing.com/search?q=crater+lake+southern+oregon&form=hpcapt&filters=HpDate%3a%2220210106_0800%22', '', '/search?q=Bing+homepage+quiz&filters=WQOskey:%22HPQuiz_20210106_SnowCraterLake%22&FORM=HPQUIZ', 'true', '3c5cb3644cac4be574893d41bcbf9ab2', 1, 1, 1, '[]', 'Travels to the Oregon deep', 'We''re looking out on the deepest lake in the US. Crater Lake, the centerpiece and namesake of the only national park in Oregon, goes down to depths of 1,943 feet—that''s enough room to stack three-and-a-half Washington Monuments end to end. Fed mainly by snowfall, this pristine, crystal blue lake came into this world with a bang. Sometime around 5700 BCE, Mount Mazama erupted, losing roughly 3,000 feet of its height. The volcano blew out so much molten rock that it left a giant depression that gradually filled with water, giving us this serene scene today. Crater Lake National Park is open to visitors year-round, but in the winter many of the facilities as well as the road circumventing the lake are closed. But, as our picture captures so beautifully, the snowy view is worth a (socially distant) trip.', '前往俄勒冈深处', '我们正望向美国最深的湖泊。火山口湖是俄勒冈州唯一国家公园的中心和同名，深达1，943英尺，足以将三个半华盛顿纪念碑堆放到一端。主要靠降雪，这个原始的，水晶蓝色的湖来到这个世界砰的一声。大约在 BCE 5700 年左右，马扎马火山爆发，失去大约 3，000 英尺的高度。火山喷出这么多熔融的岩石，留下一个巨大的凹陷，逐渐充满水，给我们今天这个宁静的景象。火山口湖国家公园全年对游客开放，但在冬季，许多设施以及绕湖道路都关闭。但是，正如我们的照片捕捉到如此美丽，雪景是值得（社会遥远的）旅行。');
INSERT INTO "picture" VALUES (184, 20210105, 202101051600, 20210106, 'https://cn.bing.com', '/th?id=OHR.SnowCraterLake_ZH-CN9218350129_1920x1080.jpg&rf=LaDigue_1920x1080.jpg&pid=hp', '/th?id=OHR.SnowCraterLake_ZH-CN9218350129_UHD.jpg&rf=LaDigue_UHD.jpg&pid=hp', '/th?id=OHR.SnowCraterLake_ZH-CN9218350129', 'OHR.SnowCraterLake_ZH-CN9218350129_1920x1080.jpg', 'OHR.SnowCraterLake_ZH-CN9218350129_UHD.jpg', '火山口湖，俄勒冈州 (© Steve Bloom Images/Alamy)', 'Red-fronted macaws in Omerque, Cochabamba, Bolivia (© Bernard Castelein/Minden Pictures)', 'https://www.bing.com/search?q=red+fronted+macaws&form=hpcapt&filters=HpDate%3a%2220210105_0800%22', '', '/search?q=Bing+homepage+quiz&filters=WQOskey:%22HPQuiz_20210105_RedFrontMacaw%22&FORM=HPQUIZ', 'true', '0597b6f2ee6914dd200beef7fec253cd', 1, 1, 1, '[]', 'Flying high on National Bird Day', 'On National Bird Day, we''re looking at two red-fronted macaws. These birds are endangered, but they''re not hard to find at the Red-Fronted Macaw Reserve in Bolivia, where this picture was taken. They''re easiest to spot during breeding season, which runs from November to May, and they usually fly in pairs or larger groups. National Bird Day is observed on January 5, which coincides with the end of the Christmas Bird Count—a citizen survey that looks at native bird populations in the US. National Bird Day puts the focus on birds around the world, especially those threatened with extinction due to the pet trade, habitat loss, and climate change.', '国家鸟日飞高', '国庆节，我们看两只红面金刚鹦鹉。这些鸟类濒临灭绝，但在玻利维亚的红头金刚鹦鹉保护区不难发现，这张照片是在那里拍摄的。在11月至5月的繁殖季节，它们最容易被发现，它们通常成对或较大的群蝇。1月5日是"国家鸟类日"，恰逢圣诞鸟类计数的结束，这是一项调查，调查美国本土鸟类种群。国家鸟类日关注世界各地的鸟类，尤其是那些因宠物贸易、栖息地丧失和气候变化而濒临灭绝的鸟类。');

